{"type":"message","id":"a3b8092b","parentId":"72f1cfe1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:24:07.972Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The spark project files weren't persisted to the workspace. The spark-ollama app is deployed on Modal, but the local files aren't in the workspace.\n\nI have two options:\n1. Ask Zach where the files are / if they were saved somewhere\n2. Rebuild what we need from scratch\n\nGiven the conversation context, the React UI was started but truncated. I should probably rebuild the complete stack:\n- modal_ollama.py (the FastAPI app on Modal with Ollama) \n- The React UI for the eval harness\n\nLet me think about what to build:\n\n1. **Modal App (modal_spark.py)** - FastAPI on Modal that:\n   - Runs Ollama with Qwen 7B\n   - Has endpoints for inference\n   - Serves a React static UI\n   - Has eval harness endpoints\n\n2. **React UI** - A React app that:\n   - Shows benchmark results\n   - Has a chat interface to the model\n   - Shows experiment results\n\nBut actually - let me first understand what already exists on Modal. The app is deployed, but I don't know the current state of the code. Let me check if I can find the deployed app's URL.\n\nFrom the previous session memory:\n```\nPOST https://spark-ollama-qwen-generate-toxzak.modal.run\n```\n\nSo the app is deployed. But the code files aren't in the workspace. I should probably:\n1. First rebuild/create the modal app with eval harness support\n2. Build the React UI\n3. Deploy\n\nLet me ask Zach - does he want me to build a fresh eval harness UI, or should I try to find what we had before?\n\nActually, looking at the flow - Zach said \"a ui would be nice\" for the eval harness. \n\nFor the eval harness specifically, I don't need to rebuild the full SPARK UI. I could create a simpler React app that:\n1. Calls a /eval endpoint on Modal\n2. Shows benchmark results\n\nBut actually - the React UI we were building before was a full chat UI. \n\nThe eval harness would be a separate view or dashboard rather than a rebuild of the entire interface. Since Zach emphasized wanting UI for the eval results, I should focus on creating a dashboard component that displays benchmark data and experiment outcomes, keeping it distinct from the broader chat functionality we discussed before.","thinkingSignature":"a8aa554baa2b08bdaa03d7cc001b7962c3c1366f2becf59231a5512272513f14"},{"type":"text","text":"\nGood news: spark-ollama is deployed on Modal. Bad news: the code files from the last session didn't get saved to the workspace — looks like they were session-only.\n\nHere's what I'll build:\n\n**1. Eval Harness on Modal** — a FastAPI endpoint that runs benchmarks against your deployed model and returns structured results\n\n**2. React Dashboard** — a simple UI served from Modal static hosting that shows:\n- Current benchmark scores\n- Run new evaluations\n- See diffs between runs\n\nThis way it's all in one place — the eval logic and the UI both live on Modal, and you get a URL you can open anywhere.\n\nLet me build it now:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0c19nxtahwfy_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\benchmarks.py","content":"\"\"\"\nBenchmark definitions for the Water Engine eval harness.\nKept simple and fast to run — expandable later.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport time\nimport json\nimport statistics\nfrom typing import Callable\n\n# GSM8K (grade school math) — strong signal for reasoning\nGSM8K_PROMPTS = [\n    \"There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the orchard today. When they finished, there were 21 trees in the orchard. How many trees did they plant today?\",\n    \"If Leah has 6 apples and 4 oranges, and she eats 2 fruits, how many fruits does she have left?\",\n    \"A clown has 12 balloons. He gives away 5 to children. Later he buys 8 more balloons. How many balloons does he have now?\",\n    \"Tom has 5 baseball cards. He buys 3 more packs with 4 cards each. How many cards does he have total?\",\n    \"There are 3 pink flowers and 4 blue flowers in a vase. Sarah puts 2 more pink flowers in the vase. How many flowers are in the vase?\",\n]\n\n# Simple reasoning prompts\nREASONING_PROMPTS = [\n    \"If all Zeps are Mors, and some Mors are Leps, could some Zeps be Leps? Explain your reasoning.\",\n    \"Complete the pattern: 2, 6, 12, 20, 30, ?\",\n    \"What is heavier: a pound of feathers or a pound of bricks?\",\n    \"If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 widgets?\",\n    \"A farmer has 17 sheep. All but 9 die. How many are left?\",\n]\n\n# Code completion (simple functions)\nCODE_PROMPTS = [\n    \"Write a Python function to check if a string is a palindrome.\",\n    \"Write a Python function that returns the nth Fibonacci number using iteration.\",\n    \"Write a Python function to find the maximum element in a list without using max().\",\n]\n\n\ndef run_benchmark(\n    generate_fn: Callable[[str], tuple[str, float]],\n    prompts: list[str],\n    name: str,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run a benchmark suite.\n    generate_fn: takes prompt string, returns (response_text, latency_seconds)\n    \"\"\"\n    results = []\n    latencies = []\n\n    for prompt in prompts:\n        start = time.perf_counter()\n        response, _ = generate_fn(prompt)\n        latency = time.perf_counter() - start\n        latencies.append(latency)\n        results.append({\n            \"prompt\": prompt,\n            \"response\": response,\n            \"latency_s\": round(latency, 3),\n        })\n\n    return {\n        \"name\": name,\n        \"num_prompts\": len(prompts),\n        \"avg_latency_s\": round(statistics.mean(latencies), 3),\n        \"total_time_s\": round(sum(latencies), 3),\n        \"results\": results,\n    }\n\n\ndef run_all_benchmarks(generate_fn: Callable[[str], tuple[str, float]]) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Run all benchmarks and return a full report.\"\"\"\n    benchmarks = [\n        (\"gsm8k\", GSM8K_PROMPTS),\n        (\"reasoning\", REASONING_PROMPTS),\n        (\"code\", CODE_PROMPTS),\n    ]\n\n    report = {\n        \"timestamp\": time.time(),\n        \"benchmarks\": [],\n    }\n\n    for name, prompts in benchmarks:\n        result = run_benchmark(generate_fn, prompts, name)\n        report[\"benchmarks\"].append(result)\n\n    return report\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11789,"output":1428,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27133,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774322610550}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d020310","parentId":"a3b8092b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:24:08.023Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0c19nxtahwfy_1","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 3023 bytes to C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\benchmarks.py"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774322648004}}
{"type":"message","id":"59d5f353","parentId":"6d020310","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:25:32.228Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me build the main Modal app that has the FastAPI server with Ollama and the eval harness endpoints, plus serves the React UI.","thinkingSignature":"21949b019a1246190de9115fe24247188b2d22a5d45369451dfbb0905979930c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_twlwv07zt4yq_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","content":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama Modal App\nFastAPI + Ollama on A100 with eval harness and React UI serving.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport json\nimport tempfile\nimport urllib.request\nimport zipfile\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport modal\n\n# ─── App definition ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\n\n# ─── Image setup ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimage = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn\", \"aiofiles\", \"jinja2\")\n    .pip_install(\"llama-stack\", \"llama-stack-client\")\n    .env({\"OLLAMA_HOST\": \"http://127.0.0.1:11434\"})\n)\n\n# ─── Volumes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nvolume = modal.Volume.from_name(\"spark-models\", create=True)\n\nMODEL_DIR = \"/models\"\nOLLAMA_PORT = 11434\n\n# ─── Model installation ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nMODEL_NAME = \"qwen2.5:7b\"\nOLLAMA_BINARY = \"\"\"\n#!/bin/bash\nexec /usr/bin/ollama serve --host 0.0.0.0 {port}\n\"\"\"\n\n@app.function(image=image, volumes={MODEL_DIR: volume}, timeout=600)\ndef pull_model():\n    \"\"\"Pull the Ollama model if not already present.\"\"\"\n    import subprocess\n    import time\n    \n    # Check if model exists\n    result = subprocess.run(\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"list\"],\n        capture_output=True, text=True\n    )\n    if MODEL_NAME in result.stdout:\n        print(f\"Model {MODEL_NAME} already present.\")\n        return\n    \n    print(f\"Pulling {MODEL_NAME}...\")\n    proc = subprocess.Popen(\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\n        stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT, text=True\n    )\n    for line in proc.stdout:\n        print(line, end=\"\")\n    proc.wait()\n    print(\"Pull complete.\")\n\n@app.function(image=image, timeout=60)\ndef ensure_ollama():\n    \"\"\"Install Ollama binary if not present.\"\"\"\n    import subprocess\n    import os\n    \n    ollama_path = \"/usr/local/bin/ollama\"\n    if os.path.exists(ollama_path):\n        return\n    \n    print(\"Installing Ollama...\")\n    result = subprocess.run(\n        [\"curl\", \"-fsSL\", \"https://ollama.com/install.sh\"],\n        capture_output=True, text=True\n    )\n    # Fallback: download release directly\n    subprocess.run([\n        \"curl\", \"-L\", \n        \"https://github.com/ollama/ollama/releases/download/v0.5.4/ollama-linux-amd64\",\n        \"-o\", ollama_path\n    ], check=True)\n    subprocess.run([\"chmod\", \"+x\", ollama_path], check=True)\n    print(\"Ollama installed.\")\n\n# ─── FastAPI app ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nweb_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn\", \"aiofiles\", \"jinja2\", \"httpx\")\n)\n\n@app.cls(image=web_image, volumes={MODEL_DIR: volume}, timeout=300, container_idle_timeout=120)\nclass Web:\n    @modal.method()\n    def generate(self, prompt: str, model: str = MODEL_NAME, temperature: float = 0.7, num_predict: int = 300):\n        \"\"\"Generate text via Ollama.\"\"\"\n        import httpx\n        \n        with httpx.Client(timeout=60.0) as client:\n            response = client.post(\n                f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                json={\n                    \"model\": model,\n                    \"prompt\": prompt,\n                    \"temperature\": temperature,\n                    \"num_predict\": num_predict,\n                    \"stream\": False,\n                }\n            )\n            response.raise_for_status()\n            return response.json()\n\n    @modal.method()\n    def benchmarks(self):\n        \"\"\"Run the eval harness and return results.\"\"\"\n        import httpx\n        import time\n        import statistics\n        from spark.benchmarks import GSM8K_PROMPTS, REASONING_PROMPTS, CODE_PROMPTS\n        \n        BENCHMARK_PROMPTS = {\n            \"gsm8k\": GSM8K_PROMPTS,\n            \"reasoning\": REASONING_PROMPTS,\n            \"code\": CODE_PROMPTS,\n        }\n        \n        results = {\"benchmarks\": [], \"timestamp\": time.time()}\n        \n        for bench_name, prompts in BENCHMARK_PROMPTS.items():\n            bench_results = []\n            latencies = []\n            \n            for prompt in prompts:\n                start = time.perf_counter()\n                try:\n                    with httpx.Client(timeout=60.0) as client:\n                        r = client.post(\n                            f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                            json={\n                                \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n                                \"prompt\": prompt,\n                                \"temperature\": 0.7,\n                                \"num_predict\": 300,\n                                \"stream\": False,\n                            }\n                        )\n                        r.raise_for_status()\n                        response_text = r.json().get(\"response\", \"\")\n                except Exception as e:\n                    response_text = f\"ERROR: {str(e)}\"\n                \n                latency = time.perf_counter() - start\n                latencies.append(latency)\n                bench_results.append({\n                    \"prompt\": prompt,\n                    \"response\": response_text,\n                    \"latency_s\": round(latency, 3),\n                })\n            \n            results[\"benchmarks\"].append({\n                \"name\": bench_name,\n                \"num_prompts\": len(prompts),\n                \"avg_latency_s\": round(statistics.mean(latencies), 3),\n                \"total_time_s\": round(sum(latencies), 3),\n                \"results\": bench_results,\n            })\n        \n        return results\n\n    @modal.method()\n    def health(self):\n        \"\"\"Health check.\"\"\"\n        import httpx\n        try:\n            with httpx.Client(timeout=5.0) as client:\n                r = client.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"status_code\": r.status_code}\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)}\n\n# ─── Static file serving (React UI) ─────────────────────────────────────────\n\nReact_TAR = \"spark-ui.tar\"\n\n@app.function(image=web_image, volumes={MODEL_DIR: volume}, timeout=300)\ndef build_react_ui():\n    \"\"\"Build the React UI and package it as a tar.\"\"\"\n    import subprocess\n    import tempfile\n    import os\n    import hashlib\n    \n    ui_dir = Path(\"/tmp/spark-ui\")\n    if ui_dir.exists():\n        subprocess.run([\"rm\", \"-rf\", str(ui_dir)])\n    ui_dir.mkdir(parents=True)\n    \n    # Write package.json\n    (ui_dir / \"package.json\").write_text(json.dumps({\n        \"name\": \"spark-ui\",\n        \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n        \"private\": True,\n        \"scripts\": {\n            \"dev\": \"vite\",\n            \"build\": \"vite build\",\n            \"preview\": \"vite preview\"\n        },\n        \"dependencies\": {\n            \"react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n            \"react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\",\n            \"axios\": \"^1.6.0\"\n        },\n        \"devDependencies\": {\n            \"@vitejs/plugin-react\": \"^4.2.0\",\n            \"vite\": \"^5.0.0\"\n        }\n    }, indent=2))\n    \n    # Write vite.config.js\n    (ui_dir / \"vite.config.js\").write_text(\"\"\"\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vite'\nimport react from '@vitejs/plugin-react'\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  plugins: [react()],\n  base: './',\n  build: {\n    outDir: 'dist',\n    emptyOutDir: true,\n  }\n})\n\"\"\")\n    \n    # Write index.html\n    (ui_dir / \"index.html\").write_text(\"\"\"\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n    <title>SPARK Eval</title>\n    <style>\n      * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n      body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; background: #0f0f13; color: #e0e0e0; min-height: 100vh; }\n      #root { padding: 2rem; max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }\n      h1 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; }\n      .card { background: #1a1a22; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; }\n      .card h2 { color: #a0a0b0; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 1rem; }\n      button { background: #6366f1; color: white; border: none; padding: 0.6rem 1.2rem; border-radius: 8px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500; }\n      button:hover { background: #4f46e5; }\n      button:disabled { background: #3a3a4a; cursor: not-allowed; }\n      .benchmark-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1rem; }\n      .benchmark-card { background: #14141c; border-radius: 8px; padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #252530; }\n      .benchmark-card h3 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }\n      .benchmark-stat { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 0.3rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #252530; font-size: 0.85rem; }\n      .benchmark-stat:last-child { border-bottom: none; }\n      .stat-label { color: #707080; }\n      .stat-value { color: #e0e0e0; font-family: monospace; }\n      .prompt-result { margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid #252530; }\n      .prompt { color: #9090a0; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }\n      .response { color: #d0d0e0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5; background: #101018; padding: 0.8rem; border-radius: 6px; margin-top: 0.5rem; }\n      .latency { color: #6366f1; font-size: 0.8rem; margin-top: 0.3rem; }\n      .loading { color: #6366f1; animation: pulse 1.5s infinite; }\n      @keyframes pulse { 0%, 100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: 0.5; } }\n      .header { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }\n      .model-badge { background: #252530; padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.8rem; color: #a0a0b0; }\n    </style>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <div id=\"root\"></div>\n    <script type=\"module\">\n      import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'\n      import ReactDOM from 'react-dom/client'\n      import axios from 'axios'\n\n      const API = window.location.origin\n\n      function App() {\n        const [benchmarks, setBenchmarks] = useState(null)\n        const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false)\n        const [health, setHealth] = useState(null)\n        const [expanded, setExpanded] = useState({})\n\n        useEffect(() => {\n          checkHealth()\n        }, [])\n\n        async function checkHealth() {\n          try {\n            const r = await axios.get(API + '/health')\n            setHealth(r.data)\n          } catch (e) {\n            setHealth({ status: 'error', error: e.message })\n          }\n        }\n\n        async function runBenchmarks() {\n          setLoading(true)\n          try {\n            const r = await axios.post(API + '/benchmarks')\n            setBenchmarks(r.data)\n          } catch (e) {\n            alert('Benchmark failed: ' + e.message)\n          }\n          setLoading(false)\n        }\n\n        function toggleExpand(bench, idx) {\n          const key = bench + '-' + idx\n          setExpanded(prev => ({ ...prev, [key]: !prev[key] }))\n        }\n\n        return (\n          <div>\n            <div className=\"header\">\n              <h1>⚡ SPARK Eval</h1>\n              <div style={{display: 'flex', gap: '1rem', alignItems: 'center'}}>\n                <span className=\"model-badge\">qwen2.5:7b</span>\n                <span style={{fontSize: '0.8rem', color: health?.status === 'ok' ? '#22c55e' : '#ef4444'}}>\n                  {health?.status === 'ok' ? '● Online' : '○ Offline'}\n                </span>\n                <button onClick={runBenchmarks} disabled={loading}>\n                  {loading ? 'Running...' : 'Run Benchmarks'}\n                </button>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n\n            {!benchmarks && !loading && (\n              <div className=\"card\">\n                <h2>Ready</h2>\n                <p style={{color: '#707080', fontSize: '0.9rem'}}>\n                  Click \"Run Benchmarks\" to evaluate the model on GSM8K math, reasoning, and code tasks.\n                </p>\n              </div>\n            )}\n\n            {benchmarks && (\n              <div>\n                <div className=\"card\">\n                  <h2>Results</h2>\n                  <p style={{color: '#707080', fontSize: '0.8rem', marginBottom: '1rem'}}>\n                    {new Date(benchmarks.timestamp * 1000).toLocaleString()}\n                  </p>\n                  <div className=\"benchmark-grid\">\n                    {benchmarks.benchmarks.map((bench) => (\n                      <div key={bench.name} className=\"benchmark-card\">\n                        <h3>{bench.name.toUpperCase()}</h3>\n                        <div className=\"benchmark-stat\">\n                          <span className=\"stat-label\">Prompts</span>\n                          <span className=\"stat-value\">{bench.num_prompts}</span>\n                        </div>\n                        <div className=\"benchmark-stat\">\n                          <span className=\"stat-label\">Avg Latency</span>\n                          <span className=\"stat-value\">{bench.avg_latency_s}s</span>\n                        </div>\n                        <div className=\"benchmark-stat\">\n                          <span className=\"stat-label\">Total Time</span>\n                          <span className=\"stat-value\">{bench.total_time_s}s</span>\n                        </div>\n                      </div>\n                    ))}\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n\n                {benchmarks.benchmarks.map((bench) => (\n                  <div key={bench.name} className=\"card\">\n                    <h2>{bench.name.toUpperCase()} — Prompts & Responses</h2>\n                    {bench.results.map((r, idx) => {\n                      const key = bench.name + '-' + idx\n                      return (\n                        <div key={idx} className=\"prompt-result\">\n                          <div style={{display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between', cursor: 'pointer'}} onClick={() => toggleExpand(bench.name, idx)}>\n                            <p className=\"prompt\">Q: {r.prompt.slice(0, 80)}{r.prompt.length > 80 ? '...' : ''}</p>\n                            <span style={{color: '#6366f1', fontSize: '0.8rem'}}>{expanded[key] ? '▲' : '▼'}</span>\n                          </div>\n                          {expanded[key] && (\n                            <div>\n                              <div className=\"response\">A: {r.response}</div>\n                              <div className=\"latency\">{r.latency_s}s</div>\n                            </div>\n                          )}\n                        </div>\n                      )\n                    })}\n                  </div>\n                ))}\n              </div>\n            )}\n          </div>\n        )\n      }\n\n      ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')).render(<App />)\n    </script>\n  </body>\n</html>\n\"\"\")\n\n    # Build with vite\n    print(\"Installing dependencies...\")\n    subprocess.run([\"npm\", \"install\"], cwd=str(ui_dir), check=True)\n    \n    print(\"Building React app...\")\n    subprocess.run([\"npm\", \"run\", \"build\"], cwd=str(ui_dir), check=True, capture_output=True, text=True)\n    \n    # Package as tar\n    print(\"Packaging...\")\n    tar_path = Path(\"/tmp/\" + React_TAR)\n    subprocess.run(\n        [\"tar\", \"cf\", str(tar_path), \"-C\", str(ui_dir / \"dist\"), \".\"],\n        check=True\n    )\n    \n    print(f\"React UI built and packaged: {tar_path}\")\n    return str(tar_path)\n\n\n# ─── Serve the app with static files ─────────────────────────────────────────\n\n@app.function(image=web_image, volumes={MODEL_DIR: volume})\ndef serve(rebuild: bool = False):\n    \"\"\"Run the Ollama server + serve FastAPI + static UI.\"\"\"\n    import subprocess\n    import time\n    import os\n\n    # Start Ollama in background\n    print(\"Starting Ollama server...\")\n    ollama_proc = subprocess.Popen(\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"serve\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", str(OLLAMA_PORT)],\n        stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT, text=True\n    )\n    \n    # Wait for Ollama to be ready\n    print(\"Waiting for Ollama...\")\n    time.sleep(5)\n    \n    # Pull model\n    pull_model()\n    \n    # Build UI\n    tar_path = build_react_ui()\n    \n    # Extract to serve dir\n    serve_dir = Path(\"/tmp/spark-static\")\n    if serve_dir.exists():\n        subprocess.run([\"rm\", \"-rf\", str(serve_dir)])\n    serve_dir.mkdir(parents=True)\n    subprocess.run([\"tar\", \"xf\", tar_path, \"-C\", str(serve_dir)], check=True)\n    \n    print(f\"UI extracted to {serve_dir}\")\n    print(f\"Ollama running on port {OLLAMA_PORT}\")\n    \n    # Keep alive\n    ollama_proc.wait()\n\n\n# ─── Local dev entrypoint ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef main():\n    # First ensure model is pulled\n    pull_model()\n    # Then start serving\n    serve.remote()\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13257,"output":4275,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31448,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774322648023}}
