{"type":"message","id":"687107b9","parentId":"ef913a1a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:25:42.264Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to actually deploy this to Modal. Let me run `modal deploy` on it. But wait - I also need Ollama installed on the Modal containers. The current approach tries to install Ollama inside the container, but that's complex. Let me think about a simpler approach.\n\nActually, looking at the existing spark-ollama app - it's already deployed and working. The issue is that we don't have the source files. Let me just deploy this new version and see what happens.\n\nActually wait - there's a problem with my approach. The `serve` function tries to start Ollama inside the container, but in Modal's sandbox environment, Ollama needs to run as a server. The current spark-ollama app might already be running Ollama.\n\nLet me try a different, simpler approach:\n\n\nI'll split this into two separate Modal apps - one that handles Ollama running on an A100 with the generate and benchmarks endpoints, and another that serves the React UI as static files. Then I can either combine them or serve the UI from a different endpoint. Actually, the simplest path forward is to just deploy what I have to Modal and see what errors come back - that way I can debug in real time rather than planning around assumptions.","thinkingSignature":"4bee20ba5e8b383f71859e538a7a102a5b2ec18fcc8b9b8b850545aec74a341f"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me deploy this to Modal:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ty8tk9wlzkv7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark; modal deploy modal_spark.py 2>&1","timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17572,"output":318,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31806,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":17743