{"type":"message","id":"45992e31","parentId":"6b5f0ed6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:25:50.013Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, the `modal.Volume.from_name()` doesn't take `create=True` - I need to use a different approach. Let me check the Modal SDK version and fix this.\n\nThe issue is that `modal.Volume.from_name()` creates a reference to an existing volume, not creates a new one. If the volume already exists (which it does - \"spark-models\"), we just need to reference it.\n\nLet me fix this - remove the `create=True` and also the Volume might not even be needed if we're just using Ollama directly from the container filesystem.","thinkingSignature":"b7e438efbea91ea23460b9b3b4e56a4cac1bde17760afeaf6332af232df0d15a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c043nm5zc30o_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","oldText":"MODEL_DIR = \"/models\"\nOLLAMA_PORT = 11434","newText":"MODEL_DIR = \"/root/.ollama\"\nOLLAMA_PORT = 11434"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18149,"output":206,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32271,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774322744014}}
