{"type":"message","id":"0ae7df96","parentId":"b38ea889","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:28:55.602Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Modal doesn't have `wsgi` - it's probably `asgi_app` or something else. Let me look at how to serve HTTP with FastAPI on Modal. Actually, Modal has `@app.function()` for web endpoints. For FastAPI, you'd use `@modal.asgi_app()` or something. Let me check.\n\nActually, looking at Modal docs, for FastAPI you use `@app.asgi_app()`. But the issue is I'm trying to mix WSGI with Modal's serving. Let me use Modal's native HTTP serving which is `@app.function()` with a web_server.\n\nActually, the simplest approach for Modal is to use their `FastAPI` support with `@app.asgi_app()`. \n\nThe real problem is I can't easily serve both the Ollama subprocess and the FastAPI endpoint together in a container without either running Ollama as a separate Modal service or embedding it in the same process. I think the right path forward is to use `@app.asgi_app()` for FastAPI and accept that Ollama needs to be managed separately.","thinkingSignature":"ffda67997b3f81397901380361c1dc6ea2b2cdf4f6840b2045823002d56da7cc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4tifujtwp0u8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark; modal deploy modal_spark.py --help 2>&1 | head -30","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":26752,"output":277,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40945,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774322927388}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd7d90df","parentId":"0ae7df96","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:28:57.335Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4tifujtwp0u8_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage: modal deploy [OPTIONS] APP_REF                                         \r\n                                                                               \r\n Deploy a Modal application.                                                   \r\n                                                                               \r\n Usage: modal deploy my_script.py modal deploy -m my_package.my_mod            \r\n                                                                               \r\n+- Arguments -----------------------------------------------------------------+\r\n| *    app_ref      TEXT  Path to a Python file with an app to deploy         |\r\n|                         [required]                                          |\r\n+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+\r\n+- Options -------------------------------------------------------------------+\r\n| --name                                 TEXT  Name of the deployment.        |\r\n| --env          -e                      TEXT  Environment to interact with.  |\r\n|                                              If not specified, Modal will   |\r\n|                                              use the default environment of |\r\n|                                              your current profile, or the   |\r\n|                                              MODAL_ENVIRONMENT variable.    |\r\n|                                              Otherwise, raises an error if  |\r\n|                                              the workspace has multiple     |\r\n|                                              environments.                  |\r\n| --stream-logs      --no-stream-logs          Stream logs from the app upon  |\r\n|                                              deployment.                    |\r\n|                                              [default: no-stream-logs]      |\r\n| --tag                                  TEXT  Tag the deployment with a      |\r\n|                                              version.                       |\r\n|                -m                            Interpret argument as a Python |\r\n|                                              module path instead of a       |\r\n|                                              file/script path               |\r\n| --timestamps                                 Show timestamps for each log   |"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1692,"aggregated":"Usage: modal deploy [OPTIONS] APP_REF                                         \r\n                                                                               \r\n Deploy a Modal application.                                                   \r\n                                                                               \r\n Usage: modal deploy my_script.py modal deploy -m my_package.my_mod            \r\n                                                                               \r\n+- Arguments -----------------------------------------------------------------+\r\n| *    app_ref      TEXT  Path to a Python file with an app to deploy         |\r\n|                         [required]                                          |\r\n+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+\r\n+- Options -------------------------------------------------------------------+\r\n| --name                                 TEXT  Name of the deployment.        |\r\n| --env          -e                      TEXT  Environment to interact with.  |\r\n|                                              If not specified, Modal will   |\r\n|                                              use the default environment of |\r\n|                                              your current profile, or the   |\r\n|                                              MODAL_ENVIRONMENT variable.    |\r\n|                                              Otherwise, raises an error if  |\r\n|                                              the workspace has multiple     |\r\n|                                              environments.                  |\r\n| --stream-logs      --no-stream-logs          Stream logs from the app upon  |\r\n|                                              deployment.                    |\r\n|                                              [default: no-stream-logs]      |\r\n| --tag                                  TEXT  Tag the deployment with a      |\r\n|                                              version.                       |\r\n|                -m                            Interpret argument as a Python |\r\n|                                              module path instead of a       |\r\n|                                              file/script path               |\r\n| --timestamps                                 Show timestamps for each log   |","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774322937316}}
{"type":"message","id":"3faf8411","parentId":"bd7d90df","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:30:17.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the Modal docs to understand how to serve HTTP. Modal supports `@app.function()` for HTTP endpoints. But for more complex apps, there's `@app.asgi_app()` for ASGI apps (FastAPI, Starlette, etc.).\n\nLet me rewrite using FastAPI as an ASGI app. Ollama would be a separate service. But actually, let me check what the existing spark-ollama app looks like since it's already deployed.\n\nActually, a simpler approach: since Ollama is already running in the existing spark-ollama container, I just need to add an API to it. But the new deployment would create a different container. \n\nI should use `@app.asgi_app()` for the FastAPI part, but I'm realizing the real issue is that deploying a new version will create fresh containers without Ollama pre-installed. I need to either include Ollama installation in the image or find a way to route to the existing Ollama instance that's already running.\n\nLet me step back and build the simplest working version first—just get a FastAPI app with Ollama running in the same container, and deploy that. I'll start with the minimal approach of installing Ollama at runtime if needed, rather than trying to pre-install it.","thinkingSignature":"0118982cf58c7a4d90d4ad44e931ad5afa2dcc3a83f6ba1619f205ac6b74ed50"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0f10f1mirnvx_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","content":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama — FastAPI + Ollama on Modal A100 with eval harness and simple UI.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport time\nimport json\nimport threading\nimport os\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\n\nOLLAMA_PORT = 11434\nMODEL_NAME = \"qwen2.5:7b\"\n\n# ─── Benchmark data (inline, no imports needed) ──────────────────────────────\n\nGSM8K_PROMPTS = [\n    \"There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the orchard today. When they finished, there were 21 trees in the orchard. How many trees did they plant today?\",\n    \"Leah has 6 apples and 4 oranges, and she eats 2 fruits. How many fruits does she have left?\",\n    \"A clown has 12 balloons. He gives away 5 to children. Later he buys 8 more balloons. How many balloons does he have now?\",\n    \"Tom has 5 baseball cards. He buys 3 more packs with 4 cards each. How many cards does he have total?\",\n    \"There are 3 pink flowers and 4 blue flowers in a vase. Sarah puts 2 more pink flowers in the vase. How many flowers are in the vase?\",\n]\n\nREASONING_PROMPTS = [\n    \"If all Zeps are Mors, and some Mors are Leps, could some Zeps be Leps? Explain your reasoning.\",\n    \"Complete the pattern: 2, 6, 12, 20, 30, ?\",\n    \"What is heavier: a pound of feathers or a pound of bricks?\",\n    \"If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 widgets?\",\n    \"A farmer has 17 sheep. All but 9 die. How many are left?\",\n]\n\nCODE_PROMPTS = [\n    \"Write a Python function to check if a string is a palindrome.\",\n    \"Write a Python function that returns the nth Fibonacci number using iteration.\",\n    \"Write a Python function to find the maximum element in a list without using max().\",\n]\n\n# ─── Ollama process management ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n_ollama_ready = False\n\ndef start_ollama():\n    global _ollama_ready\n    import httpx\n\n    # Check if already running\n    try:\n        with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as client:\n            r = client.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n            if r.status_code == 200:\n                print(\"Ollama already running.\")\n                _ollama_ready = True\n                return\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n\n    print(\"Starting Ollama server...\")\n    subprocess.Popen(\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"serve\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", str(OLLAMA_PORT)],\n        stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n        stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n    )\n\n    # Wait for it to come up\n    for i in range(30):\n        try:\n            with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as client:\n                r = client.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                if r.status_code == 200:\n                    print(\"Ollama ready!\")\n                    _ollama_ready = True\n                    return\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n        time.sleep(2)\n\n    raise RuntimeError(\"Ollama failed to start\")\n\n\ndef ensure_model():\n    import subprocess\n    result = subprocess.run(\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"list\"],\n        capture_output=True, text=True\n    )\n    if MODEL_NAME in result.stdout:\n        print(f\"Model {MODEL_NAME} already present.\")\n        return\n    print(f\"Pulling {MODEL_NAME}...\")\n    proc = subprocess.Popen(\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\n        stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT, text=True\n    )\n    for line in proc.stdout:\n        print(line, end=\"\")\n    proc.wait()\n    print(\"Model pull complete.\")\n\n\n# ─── FastAPI app ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nweb_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn[standard]\", \"httpx\")\n)\n\n@app.cls(image=web_image, timeout=600, scaledown_window=300)\nclass Web:\n    @modal.builder()\n    def builder(self):\n        import os\n        # Install Ollama in the container image\n        print(\"Installing Ollama...\")\n        subprocess.run([\"bash\", \"-c\", \"curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\"], check=True)\n        # Pre-pull model so it's available at runtime\n        subprocess.run([\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME], check=True)\n        # Install uvicorn\n        subprocess.run([\"pip\", \"install\", \"fastapi\", \"uvicorn[standard]\", \"httpx\"], check=True)\n\n    @modal.method()\n    def generate(self, prompt: str, temperature: float = 0.7, num_predict: int = 300):\n        import httpx\n        start_ollama()\n        with httpx.Client(timeout=60.0) as client:\n            r = client.post(\n                f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                json={\n                    \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n                    \"prompt\": prompt,\n                    \"temperature\": temperature,\n                    \"num_predict\": num_predict,\n                    \"stream\": False,\n                }\n            )\n            r.raise_for_status()\n            return r.json()\n\n    @modal.method()\n    def benchmarks(self):\n        import httpx\n        import statistics\n        start_ollama()\n\n        BENCHMARK_PROMPTS = {\n            \"gsm8k\": GSM8K_PROMPTS,\n            \"reasoning\": REASONING_PROMPTS,\n            \"code\": CODE_PROMPTS,\n        }\n\n        results = {\"benchmarks\": [], \"timestamp\": time.time()}\n\n        for bench_name, prompts in BENCHMARK_PROMPTS.items():\n            bench_results = []\n            latencies = []\n\n            for prompt in prompts:\n                start = time.perf_counter()\n                try:\n                    with httpx.Client(timeout=60.0) as client:\n                        r = client.post(\n                            f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                            json={\n                                \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n                                \"prompt\": prompt,\n                                \"temperature\": 0.7,\n                                \"num_predict\": 300,\n                                \"stream\": False,\n                            }\n                        )\n                        r.raise_for_status()\n                        response_text = r.json().get(\"response\", \"\")\n                except Exception as e:\n                    response_text = f\"ERROR: {str(e)}\"\n\n                latency = time.perf_counter() - start\n                latencies.append(latency)\n                bench_results.append({\n                    \"prompt\": prompt,\n                    \"response\": response_text,\n                    \"latency_s\": round(latency, 3),\n                })\n\n            results[\"benchmarks\"].append({\n                \"name\": bench_name,\n                \"num_prompts\": len(prompts),\n                \"avg_latency_s\": round(statistics.mean(latencies), 3),\n                \"total_time_s\": round(sum(latencies), 3),\n                \"results\": bench_results,\n            })\n\n        return results\n\n    @modal.method()\n    def health(self):\n        import httpx\n        try:\n            with httpx.Client(timeout=5.0) as client:\n                r = client.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"status_code\": r.status_code}\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)}\n\n    @modal.web_endpoint(methods=[\"GET\"])\n    def ui(self):\n        import json as _json\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"message\": \"See POST /benchmarks and POST /generate\",\n            \"benchmarks_url\": \"/benchmarks\",\n            \"generate_url\": \"/generate\",\n            \"health_url\": \"/health\",\n        }\n\n\n# ─── Standalone web server (for development) ─────────────────────────────────\n\nFASTAPI_HTML = \"\"\"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\"/>\n<title>SPARK Eval</title>\n<style>\n*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}\nbody{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;background:#0f0f13;color:#e0e0e0;min-height:100vh}\n#root{padding:2rem;max-width:1200px;margin:0 auto}\nh1{color:#fff;margin-bottom:1.5rem;font-weight:600}\n.card{background:#1a1a22;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border:1px solid #2a2a35}\n.card h2{color:#a0a0b0;font-size:.85rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:1rem}\nbutton{background:#6366f1;color:white;border:none;padding:.6rem 1.2rem;border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer;font-size:.9rem;font-weight:500}\nbutton:hover{background:#4f46e5}\nbutton:disabled{background:#3a3a4a;cursor:not-allowed}\n.benchmark-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(280px,1fr));gap:1rem;margin-top:1rem}\n.benchmark-card{background:#14141c;border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;border:1px solid #252530}\n.benchmark-card h3{color:#fff;margin-bottom:.5rem}\n.benchmark-stat{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:.3rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #252530;font-size:.85rem}\n.benchmark-stat:last-child{border-bottom:none}\n.stat-label{color:#707080}\n.stat-value{color:#e0e0e0;font-family:monospace}\n.prompt-result{margin-top:1rem;padding-top:1rem;border-top:1px solid #252530}\n.prompt{color:#9090a0;font-size:.85rem;margin-bottom:.5rem}\n.response{color:#d0d0e0;font-size:.9rem;line-height:1.5;background:#101018;padding:.8rem;border-radius:6px;margin-top:.5rem;white-space:pre-wrap}\n.latency{color:#6366f1;font-size:.8rem;margin-top:.3rem}\n.header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-bottom:2rem;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem}\n.model-badge{background:#252530;padding:.4rem .8rem;border-radius:6px;font-size:.8rem;color:#a0a0b0}\n.gen-form{display:flex;gap:.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem}\n.gen-form input{flex:1;background:#14141c;border:1px solid #252530;color:#e0e0e0;padding:.6rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:.9rem}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div id=\"root\"></div>\n<script type=\"module\">\nimport React,{useState,useEffect}from'react';import ReactDOM from'react-dom/client';import axios from'axios'\nconst API=''\nconst App=()=>{\n  const[benchmarks,setBenchmarks]=useState(null)\n  const[loading,setLoading]=useState(false)\n  const[health,setHealth]=useState(null)\n  const[expanded,setExpanded]=useState({})\n  const[prompt,setPrompt]=useState('')\n  const[genResult,setGenResult]=useState(null)\n  const[generating,setGenerating]=useState(false)\n  useEffect(()=>{(async()=>{try{const r=await axios.get(API+'/health');setHealth(r.data)}catch(e){setHealth({status:'error',error:e.message})}})()},[])\n  async function runBenchmarks(){setLoading(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+'/benchmarks');setBenchmarks(r.data)}catch(e){alert('Failed: '+e.message)};setLoading(false)}\n  async function generate(e){e.preventDefault();if(!prompt.trim())return;setGenerating(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+'/generate',{prompt,temperature:.7,num_predict:300});setGenResult(r.data)}catch(e){alert('Failed: '+e.message)};setGenerating(false)}\n  function toggle(b,i){const k=b+'-'+i;setExpanded(p=>({...p,[k]:!p[k]}))}\n  return React.createElement('div',null,\n    React.createElement('div',{className:'header'},\n      React.createElement('h1',null,'⚡ SPARK Eval'),\n      React.createElement('div',{style:{display:'flex',gap:'1rem',alignItems:'center',flexWrap:'wrap'}},\n        React.createElement('span',{className:'model-badge'},'qwen2.5:7b'),\n        React.createElement('span',{style:{color:health?.status==='ok'?'#22c55e':'#ef4444'}},health?.status==='ok'?'● Online':'○ '+(health?.error||'Offline')),\n        React.createElement('button',{onClick:runBenchmarks,disabled:loading},loading?'⏳ Running...':'Run Benchmarks')\n      )\n    ),\n    React.createElement('div',{className:'card'},\n      React.createElement('h2',null,'Chat'),\n      React.createElement('form',{className:'gen-form',onSubmit:generate},\n        React.createElement('input',{value:prompt,onChange:e=>setPrompt(e.target.value),placeholder:'Ask the model...'}),\n        React.createElement('button',{type:'submit',disabled:generating},generating?'...':'Send')\n      ),\n      genResult&&React.createElement('div',{className:'response'},genResult.response)\n    ),\n    benchmarks&&React.createElement('div',null,\n      React.createElement('div',{className:'card'},\n        React.createElement('h2',null,'Results — '+new Date(benchmarks.timestamp*1000).toLocaleString()),\n        React.createElement('div',{className:'benchmark-grid'},\n          benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement('div',{key:b.name,className:'benchmark-card'},\n            React.createElement('h3',null,b.name.toUpperCase()),\n            React.createElement('div',{className:'benchmark-stat'},React.createElement('span',{className:'stat-label'},'Prompts'),React.createElement('span',{className:'stat-value'},b.num_prompts)),\n            React.createElement('div',{className:'benchmark-stat'},React.createElement('span',{className:'stat-label'},'Avg Latency'),React.createElement('span',{className:'stat-value'},b.avg_latency_s+'s')),\n            React.createElement('div',{className:'benchmark-stat'},React.createElement('span',{className:'stat-label'},'Total'),React.createElement('span',{className:'stat-value'},b.total_time_s+'s'))\n          ))\n        )\n      ),\n      benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement('div',{key:b.name,className:'card'},\n        React.createElement('h2',null,b.name.toUpperCase()+' — Responses'),\n        b.results.map((r,i)=>{\n          const k=b.name+'-'+i\n          return React.createElement('div',{key:i,className:'prompt-result'},\n            React.createElement('div',{style:{display:'flex',justifyContent:'space-between',cursor:'pointer'},onClick:()=>toggle(b.name,i)},\n              React.createElement('p',{className:'prompt'},'Q: '+r.prompt.slice(0,90)+(r.prompt.length>90?'...':'')),\n              React.createElement('span',{style:{color:'#6366f1',fontSize:'.8rem'}},expanded[k]?'▲':'▼')\n            ),\n            expanded[k]&&React.createElement('div',null,\n              React.createElement('div',{className:'response'},'A: '+r.response),\n              React.createElement('div',{className:'latency'},r.latency_s+'s')\n            )\n          )\n        })\n      ))\n    ),\n    !benchmarks&&!loading&&React.createElement('div',{className:'card'},\n      React.createElement('h2',null,'Ready'),\n      React.createElement('p',{style:{color:'#707080',fontSize:'.9rem'}},'Click \"Run Benchmarks\" to evaluate the model.')\n    )\n  )\n}\nReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')).render(React.createElement(App))\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>\"\"\"\n\n\n@app.function(image=web_image)\ndef get_index_html():\n    return FASTAPI_HTML\n\n\n@app.asgi_app(image=web_image, title=\"SPARK Eval\")\ndef api():\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n\n    api = FastAPI()\n\n    @api.get(\"/\")\n    async def root():\n        return HTMLResponse(content=FASTAPI_HTML, status_code=200)\n\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        return await Web.health.remote.aio()\n\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\n    async def benchmarks():\n        return await Web.benchmarks.remote.aio()\n\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\n    async def generate(req: dict):\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\n        return await Web.generate.remote.aio(prompt=prompt, temperature=temperature, num_predict=num_predict)\n\n    return api\n\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef main():\n    print(\"SPARK Ollama — deployed via 'modal deploy'\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":27336,"output":4258,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45510,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774322937337}}
