{"type":"message","id":"3947f178","parentId":"3bc1850e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:30:28.908Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `@modal.builder()` approach installs Ollama at build time of the container. This is fine for one-time builds. But it's a heavy image. Let me also think about whether this will actually work - Ollama in a Modal container needs to be able to download models, and the `pull` command might take too long for the builder timeout.Actually, Ollama downloads models at runtime, not build time. The `pull` in `builder()` might work if it's fast enough, but it could also time out.Let me separate concerns:\n1. The ASGI FastAPI app handles HTTP requests\n2. The Web class methods call Ollama which might be running in the same container or elsewhere\n\n\nI'm realizing the ASGI app runs in its own container while Web methods run separately, so I'd need to either have both Ollama and the app in the same container, or have Web methods route elsewhere. A simpler setup would be to run everything in one container with Ollama and the web server together, though Modal's serverless functions can't really do background processes cleanly.\n\nActually, I should just deploy this and see what errors come up rather than overthinking it further.","thinkingSignature":"367cf6f38087eb1675407ad85026ec4b2407840df9ba229ed2fb3cab35bcfb7d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ed6a5qafihin_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark; modal deploy modal_spark.py 2>&1","timeout":600}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31635,"output":296,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45847,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774323017786}}
