{"type":"message","id":"b3a5150c","parentId":"9970ec7e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:31:52.837Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, there's a problem with this approach. The `@app.asgi_app()` runs in a separate container from the Web class methods. So the Ollama subprocess started from the ASGI app won't be accessible to Web methods (and vice versa). Actually, since everything is going through the ASGI app endpoints... actually I removed the Web class entirely. All the methods are now in the ASGI app itself. Let me check - yes, I removed the `@app.cls()` Web class. Now the generate and benchmarks endpoints are directly in the ASGI app and they call `start_ollama()` and `pull_model()` which manage Ollama as a subprocess in the same container.\nThis should work - the ASGI app container installs Ollama via the base image, starts it as a subprocess, and serves both the UI and the API endpoints. The only concern is whether Ollama's install script will run properly in Modal's environment.","thinkingSignature":"f2f1f75884d73635395bd7105c35d96eba9e29c14653935fa6ed388d29433b6b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jp3itp45zcjx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark; modal deploy modal_spark.py 2>&1","timeout":600}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":36190,"output":249,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50355,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774323104800}}
