{"type":"message","id":"72a1fdec","parentId":"2d0693f9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:32:09.756Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_a481hogtfzj7_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\Python\\Python314\\site-packages\\modal\\_utils\\async_utils.py:45: DeprecationWarning: 'asyncio.WindowsSelectorEventLoopPolicy' is deprecated and slated for removal in Python 3.16\r\n  asyncio.set_event_loop_policy(asyncio.WindowsSelectorEventLoopPolicy())\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\Python\\Python314\\site-packages\\modal\\_utils\\async_utils.py:45: DeprecationWarning: 'asyncio.set_event_loop_policy' is deprecated and slated for removal in Python 3.16\r\n  asyncio.set_event_loop_policy(asyncio.WindowsSelectorEventLoopPolicy())\r\nHelp on function asgi_app in module modal.partial_function:\r\n\r\nasgi_app(\r\n    _warn_parentheses_missing=None,\r\n    *,\r\n    label: Optional[str] = None,\r\n    custom_domains: Optional[Iterable[str]] = None,\r\n    requires_proxy_auth: bool = False\r\n) -> Callable[[Union[_PartialFunction, NullaryFuncOrMethod]], _PartialFunction]\r\n    Decorator for registering an ASGI app with a Modal function.\r\n\r\n    Asynchronous Server Gateway Interface (ASGI) is a standard for Python\r\n    synchronous and asynchronous apps, supported by all popular Python web\r\n    libraries. This is an advanced decorator that gives full flexibility in\r\n    defining one or more web endpoints on Modal.\r\n\r\n    **Usage:**\r\n\r\n    ```python\r\n    from typing import Callable\r\n\r\n    @app.function()\r\n    @modal.asgi_app()\r\n    def create_asgi() -> Callable:\r\n        ...\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n    To learn how to use Modal with popular web frameworks, see the\r\n    [guide on web endpoints](https://modal.com/docs/guide/webhooks)."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1080,"aggregated":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\Python\\Python314\\site-packages\\modal\\_utils\\async_utils.py:45: DeprecationWarning: 'asyncio.WindowsSelectorEventLoopPolicy' is deprecated and slated for removal in Python 3.16\r\n  asyncio.set_event_loop_policy(asyncio.WindowsSelectorEventLoopPolicy())\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\Python\\Python314\\site-packages\\modal\\_utils\\async_utils.py:45: DeprecationWarning: 'asyncio.set_event_loop_policy' is deprecated and slated for removal in Python 3.16\r\n  asyncio.set_event_loop_policy(asyncio.WindowsSelectorEventLoopPolicy())\r\nHelp on function asgi_app in module modal.partial_function:\r\n\r\nasgi_app(\r\n    _warn_parentheses_missing=None,\r\n    *,\r\n    label: Optional[str] = None,\r\n    custom_domains: Optional[Iterable[str]] = None,\r\n    requires_proxy_auth: bool = False\r\n) -> Callable[[Union[_PartialFunction, NullaryFuncOrMethod]], _PartialFunction]\r\n    Decorator for registering an ASGI app with a Modal function.\r\n\r\n    Asynchronous Server Gateway Interface (ASGI) is a standard for Python\r\n    synchronous and asynchronous apps, supported by all popular Python web\r\n    libraries. This is an advanced decorator that gives full flexibility in\r\n    defining one or more web endpoints on Modal.\r\n\r\n    **Usage:**\r\n\r\n    ```python\r\n    from typing import Callable\r\n\r\n    @app.function()\r\n    @modal.asgi_app()\r\n    def create_asgi() -> Callable:\r\n        ...\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n    To learn how to use Modal with popular web frameworks, see the\r\n    [guide on web endpoints](https://modal.com/docs/guide/webhooks).","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774323129734}}
{"type":"message","id":"3bcd7342","parentId":"72a1fdec","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:33:15.299Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see — `modal.asgi_app()` is a decorator that should be applied to a function inside a Modal app, not to the app itself. The correct usage is:\n\n```python\n@app.function()\n@modal.asgi_app()\ndef api():\n    ...\n```\n\nBut wait, the `@app.function()` creates a function, and then `@modal.asgi_app()` wraps it as an ASGI app. Let me try this approach.\n\nAlso I need to figure out the image — the ASGI app runs in its own container, so Ollama needs to be installed there too. I'll use the same `_image` with Ollama installation.\n\nLet me rewrite properly.","thinkingSignature":"265724806034ba8ad6bf402c0a57983d12e6539dfa2f992cde910219bae0d39a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7504xa5z1cfk_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","content":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama — FastAPI + Ollama + Eval Harness on Modal A100.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport time\nimport statistics\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\nOLLAMA_PORT = 11434\nMODEL_NAME = \"qwen2.5:7b\"\n\n# ─── Benchmark prompts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nGSM8K = [\n    \"There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the orchard today. When they finished, there were 21 trees in the orchard. How many trees did they plant today?\",\n    \"Leah has 6 apples and 4 oranges, and she eats 2 fruits. How many fruits does she have left?\",\n    \"A clown has 12 balloons. He gives away 5 to children. Later he buys 8 more balloons. How many balloons does he have now?\",\n    \"Tom has 5 baseball cards. He buys 3 more packs with 4 cards each. How many cards does he have total?\",\n    \"There are 3 pink flowers and 4 blue flowers in a vase. Sarah puts 2 more pink flowers in the vase. How many flowers are in the vase?\",\n]\n\nREASONING = [\n    \"If all Zeps are Mors, and some Mors are Leps, could some Zeps be Leps? Explain your reasoning.\",\n    \"Complete the pattern: 2, 6, 12, 20, 30, ?\",\n    \"What is heavier: a pound of feathers or a pound of bricks?\",\n    \"If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 widgets?\",\n    \"A farmer has 17 sheep. All but 9 die. How many are left?\",\n]\n\nCODE = [\n    \"Write a Python function to check if a string is a palindrome.\",\n    \"Write a Python function that returns the nth Fibonacci number using iteration.\",\n    \"Write a Python function to find the maximum element in a list without using max().\",\n]\n\n# ─── Ollama helpers (run in same container as ASGI app) ────────────────────\n\n_ollama_ready = [False]  # mutable flag\n\ndef start_ollama():\n    import httpx\n    try:\n        with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\n            r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n            if r.status_code == 200:\n                _ollama_ready[0] = True\n                return\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n\n    print(\"Starting Ollama server...\")\n    subprocess.Popen(\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"serve\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", str(OLLAMA_PORT)],\n        stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL, stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n    )\n    for _ in range(30):\n        try:\n            with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\n                r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                if r.status_code == 200:\n                    print(\"Ollama ready.\")\n                    _ollama_ready[0] = True\n                    return\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n        time.sleep(2)\n    raise RuntimeError(\"Ollama failed to start\")\n\n\ndef ensure_model():\n    result = subprocess.run([\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"list\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\n    if MODEL_NAME not in result.stdout:\n        print(f\"Pulling {MODEL_NAME} (this may take a few minutes)...\")\n        proc = subprocess.Popen([\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\n                                stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT, text=True)\n        for line in proc.stdout:\n            print(line, end=\"\", flush=True)\n        proc.wait()\n        print(\"Model ready.\")\n\n\n# ─── Image: Ollama + FastAPI deps ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn[standard]\", \"httpx\")\n    .run_function(\n        lambda: subprocess.run(\n            [\"bash\", \"-c\", \"curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\"],\n            check=True, capture_output=True,\n        )\n    )\n)\n\n# ─── UI HTML ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nUI_HTML = \"\"\"<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"/><title>SPARK Eval</title><style>\n*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;background:#0f0f13;color:#e0e0e0;min-height:100vh}\n#root{padding:2rem;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}h1{color:#fff;margin-bottom:1.5rem}\n.card{background:#1a1a22;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border:1px solid #2a2a35}\n.card h2{color:#a0a0b0;font-size:.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:1rem}\nbutton{background:#6366f1;color:white;border:none;padding:.6rem 1.2rem;border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer;font-size:.9rem;font-weight:500}\nbutton:hover{background:#4f46e5}button:disabled{background:#3a3a4a;cursor:not-allowed}\n.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:.75rem}\n.stat-card{background:#14141c;border-radius:8px;padding:.9rem;border:1px solid #252530}\n.stat-card h3{color:#fff;margin-bottom:.4rem;font-size:.95rem}\n.s{color:#707080;font-size:.82rem;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:.2rem 0}\n.s span{color:#c0c0d0;font-family:monospace}\n.res{margin-top:.8rem;padding-top:.8rem;border-top:1px solid #252530}\n.q{color:#888898;font-size:.82rem;margin-bottom:.4rem}\n.a{color:#d0d0e0;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.5;background:#101018;padding:.7rem;border-radius:6px;white-space:pre-wrap}\n.lat{color:#6366f1;font-size:.75rem;margin-top:.3rem}\n.expander{cursor:pointer;padding:.4rem 0}.expander:hover{color:#fff}\n.header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-bottom:2rem;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.8rem}\n.badge{background:#252530;padding:.35rem .75rem;border-radius:6px;font-size:.78rem;color:#a0a0b0}\ninput{background:#14141c;border:1px solid #252530;color:#e0e0e0;padding:.6rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:.9rem;flex:1}\n.gen-form{display:flex;gap:.5rem;margin-bottom:.8rem}\n.status{font-size:.8rem}.ok{color:#22c55e}.err{color:#ef4444}\n</style></head><body><div id=\"root\"></div>\n<script type=\"module\">\nimport React,{useState,useEffect}from\"react\";import ReactDOM from\"react-dom/client\";import axios from\"axios\"\nconst API=\"\"\nconst App=()=>{\n  const[benchmarks,setBenchmarks]=useState(null)\n  const[loading,setLoading]=useState(false)\n  const[health,setHealth]=useState(null)\n  const[expanded,setExpanded]=useState({})\n  const[prompt,setPrompt]=useState(\"\")\n  const[genResult,setGenResult]=useState(null)\n  const[genning,setGening]=useState(false)\n  useEffect(()=>{(async()=>{try{const r=await axios.get(API+\"/health\");setHealth(r.data)}catch(e){setHealth({status:\"error\",error:e.message})}})()},[])\n  const run=async()=>{setLoading(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/benchmarks\");setBenchmarks(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setLoading(false)}\n  const send=async(e)=>{e.preventDefault();if(!prompt.trim())return;setGening(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/generate\",{prompt,temperature:.7,num_predict:300});setGenResult(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setGening(false)}\n  const toggle=(b,i)=>{const k=b+\"-\"+i;setExpanded(p=>({...p,[k]:!p[k]}))}\n  return React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"header\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h1\",null,\"⚡ SPARK Eval\"),\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{style:{display:\"flex\",gap:\"1rem\",alignItems:\"center\"}},\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"badge\"},\"qwen2.5:7b\"),\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"status \"+((health?.status===\"ok\")?\"ok\":\"err\")},health?.status===\"ok\"?\"● Online\":\"○ \"+(health?.error||\"Offline\")),\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{onClick:run,disabled:loading},loading?\"⏳ Running...\":\"Run Benchmarks\")\n      )\n    ),\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Chat\"),\n      React.createElement(\"form\",{className:\"gen-form\",onSubmit:send},\n        React.createElement(\"input\",{value:prompt,onChange:e=>setPrompt(e.target.value),placeholder:\"Ask the model...\"}),\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{type:\"submit\",disabled:genning},genning?\"...\":\"Send\")\n      ),\n      genResult&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},genResult.response)\n    ),\n    benchmarks&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Results — \"+new Date(benchmarks.timestamp*1000).toLocaleString()),\n        React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"grid\"},\n          benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"stat-card\"},\n            React.createElement(\"h3\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Prompts\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.num_prompts)),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Avg Latency\"),React.createEleme