{"type":"message","id":"11464975","parentId":"3a536e84","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:34:37.786Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - I should also check whether we need to add the `nvidia-container-toolkit` for GPU support. Let me check what GPU setup Modal uses. Modal containers on A100 should have CUDA available, but Ollama needs the right environment.Let me just add zstd for now and try again. Actually, let me also consider: Ollama's install script might do more than just download a binary - it might set up systemd services or other things. For a container environment, I should just download the binary directly rather than using the install script.\n\nLet me simplify - just download the Ollama binary directly:","thinkingSignature":"175dc36924bf40c7558bb9782fe9a78e566df1ab362b34a86ae9f2a3fd2e7af9"},{"type":"text","text":"Actually let me just download Ollama directly instead of using the install script:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3y80ytujkci3_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","oldText":"    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd\",\n        \"curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )","newText":"    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl\",\n        \"curl -fsSL https://github.com/ollama/ollama/releases/download/v0.5.4/ollama-linux-amd64 -o /usr/local/bin/ollama\",\n        \"chmod +x /usr/local/bin/ollama\",\n    )"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46981,"output":315,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61212,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774323268488}}
