{"type":"message","id":"3600de1b","parentId":"1c859333","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:35:07.312Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The release page didn't show me the actual asset names. Let me try a different approach - the Ollama download page. But actually, let me try a different approach altogether: use the Modal A100 which should already have GPU support, but instead of running Ollama in a container, let me try using the Ollama API directly that Modal might expose.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read what we already have deployed. The previous spark-ollama app is already running with Ollama. Let me just use that existing Ollama endpoint.\n\nLooking at what I found earlier: the deployed app `spark-ollama` had endpoints at:\n- `https://spark-ollama-qwen-generate-{workspace}.modal.run`  \n\n\n- The existing app uses Ollama\n\nSo the simplest approach is to leverage what's already running instead of deploying a new one. For the eval harness, I just need to call that existing Ollama API. But wait, Zach wants a React UI for it too, and that's what I've been building. So I should just update the existing spark-ollama deployment to include the FastAPI routes and UI rather than spinning up something new.\n\nActually, the existing spark-ollama was deployed with a different code structure, so I don't have visibility into how it was set up. Let me take a step back - the real priority is getting the UI deployed somewhere accessible. I'll build a lightweight web server that calls the existing Ollama endpoint and serves the React UI, keeping things simple by not trying to manage Ollama myself.\n\nThe app is deployed now - let me just test whether it's actually working.","thinkingSignature":"d7bfae38f1b8a7d11ede4d988d03a5b993ecf15b4a81a503b267f0356903694a"},{"type":"text","text":"The app is already deployed. Let me test the existing endpoint and see if it's responding:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4ndqc0s3dnml_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama.modal.run/health 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49636,"output":401,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63953,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774323293274}}
{"type":"message","id":"08caa29f","parentId":"3600de1b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:35:12.753Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4ndqc0s3dnml_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"status\":\"error\",\"error\":\"'AsyncClient' object does not support the context manager protocol\"}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5401,"aggregated":"{\"status\":\"error\",\"error\":\"'AsyncClient' object does not support the context manager protocol\"}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774323312734}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c8d5d68","parentId":"08caa29f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:35:42.785Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ASGI app is running but there's an error with httpx AsyncClient usage. The issue is `httpx.AsyncClient` uses `async with` in async context, but I'm using `with` (sync context manager). Let me fix that in the health endpoint.\n\nWait, looking at the code:\n```python\nwith httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=5.0) as c:\n```\n\nThat's the issue - `AsyncClient` is async, so it needs `async with`. Let me fix all the async endpoints.","thinkingSignature":"2d7a7b3795542d040ee53f2c915fa327c23d527679113b543bdd2751121d0145"},{"type":"text","text":"The app is live but there's a bug in the async httpx calls. Let me fix:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pr7zqo1eopd8_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","oldText":"    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        try:\n            with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=5.0) as c:\n                r = await c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"code\": r.status_code}\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)}\n\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\n    async def generate(req: dict):\n        start_ollama()\n        ensure_model()\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\n        with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n            r = await c.post(\n                f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                      \"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": num_predict, \"stream\": False}\n            )\n            r.raise_for_status()\n            return r.json()\n\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\n    async def benchmarks():\n        start_ollama()\n        ensure_model()\n        BENCHMARK_PROMPTS = {\"gsm8k\": GSM8K, \"reasoning\": REASONING, \"code\": CODE}\n        results = {\"benchmarks\": [], \"timestamp\": time.time()}\n        for bench_name, prompts in BENCHMARK_PROMPTS.items():\n            bench_results, latencies = [], []\n            for prompt in prompts:\n                t0 = time.perf_counter()\n                try:\n                    with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n                        r = await c.post(\n                            f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                            json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                                  \"temperature\": 0.7, \"num_predict\": 300, \"stream\": False}\n                        )\n                        r.raise_for_status()\n                        response_text = r.json().get(\"response\", \"\")\n                except Exception as e:\n                    response_text = f\"ERROR: {str(e)}\"\n                latency = time.perf_counter() - t0\n                latencies.append(latency)\n                bench_results.append({\"prompt\": prompt, \"response\": response_text, \"latency_s\": round(latency, 3)})\n            results[\"benchmarks\"].append({\n                \"name\": bench_name, \"num_prompts\": len(prompts),\n                \"avg_latency_s\": round(statistics.mean(latencies), 3),\n                \"total_time_s\": round(sum(latencies), 3), \"results\": bench_results,\n            })\n        return results","newText":"    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        try:\n            async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=5.0) as c:\n                r = await c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"code\": r.status_code}\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)}\n\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\n    async def generate(req: dict):\n        start_ollama()\n        ensure_model()\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n            r = await c.post(\n                f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                      \"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": num_predict, \"stream\": False}\n            )\n            r.raise_for_status()\n            return r.json()\n\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\n    async def benchmarks():\n        start_ollama()\n        ensure_model()\n        BENCHMARK_PROMPTS = {\"gsm8k\": GSM8K, \"reasoning\": REASONING, \"code\": CODE}\n        results = {\"benchmarks\": [], \"timestamp\": time.time()}\n        for bench_name, prompts in BENCHMARK_PROMPTS.items():\n            bench_results, latencies = [], []\n            for prompt in prompts:\n                t0 = time.perf_counter()\n                try:\n                    async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n                        r = await c.post(\n                            f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                            json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                                  \"temperature\": 0.7, \"num_predict\": 300, \"stream\": False}\n                        )\n                        r.raise_for_status()\n                        response_text = r.json().get(\"response\", \"\")\n                except Exception as e:\n                    response_text = f\"ERROR: {str(e)}\"\n                latency = time.perf_counter() - t0\n                latencies.append(latency)\n                bench_results.append({\"prompt\": prompt, \"response\": response_text, \"latency_s\": round(latency, 3)})\n            results[\"benchmarks\"].append({\n                \"name\": bench_name, \"num_prompts\": len(prompts),\n                \"avg_latency_s\": round(statistics.mean(latencies), 3),\n                \"total_time_s\": round(sum(latencies), 3), \"results\": bench_results,\n            })\n        return results"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50073,"output":1347,"cacheRead":13916,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65336,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774323312755}}
