{"type":"message","id":"815b8f51","parentId":"70558114","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:21:16.723Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the app is deployed but the health check is failing because of the AsyncClient issue. The problem is that `httpx.AsyncClient` is being used with `async with` but maybe there's a version issue. Let me look at the current state of the modal_spark.py file to understand what needs to be fixed.\n\nThe issue is `async with httpx.AsyncClient(...)` - the version of httpx installed in the Modal image might not support this syntax, or there's some issue.\n\nLet me check the deployed URL and see if the web UI at least loads.","thinkingSignature":"d8bbfa27d9e98644d9d35ed0b8a8ccfc613160c3f6e61915575028f1a1cc8a71"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v81rk4qw0lfm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama.modal.run/ 2>&1 | head -5","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73057,"output":175,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87224,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326071805}}
{"type":"message","id":"dfa3f253","parentId":"815b8f51","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:21:20.143Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_v81rk4qw0lfm_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"/><title>SPARK Eval</title><style>\r\n*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;background:#0f0f13;color:#e0e0e0;min-height:100vh}\r\n#root{padding:2rem;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}h1{color:#fff;margin-bottom:1.5rem}\r\n.card{background:#1a1a22;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border:1px solid #2a2a35}\r\n.card h2{color:#a0a0b0;font-size:.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:1rem}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3321,"aggregated":"<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"/><title>SPARK Eval</title><style>\r\n*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;background:#0f0f13;color:#e0e0e0;min-height:100vh}\r\n#root{padding:2rem;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}h1{color:#fff;margin-bottom:1.5rem}\r\n.card{background:#1a1a22;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border:1px solid #2a2a35}\r\n.card h2{color:#a0a0b0;font-size:.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:1rem}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326080074}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ed1765d","parentId":"dfa3f253","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:21:28.673Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The web UI is loading! The HTML is being served correctly. The issue is the `/health`, `/benchmarks`, and `/generate` endpoints that use httpx.AsyncClient with `async with`. The problem is that `httpx.AsyncClient` in the version installed doesn't support the context manager protocol in the way we're using it, OR there's an issue with how Modal's ASGI app is set up.\n\nActually, looking at the error message: `'AsyncClient' object does not support the context manager protocol` - this is happening because the version of httpx installed might be 0.x which uses `async with Client()` not `AsyncClient`. But we're using `httpx.AsyncClient` which should work in 0.28...\n \nThe deployed app might still be running the old image with the buggy code even though we fixed it and redeployed. The `async with httpx.AsyncClient()` pattern is correct for httpx 0.28+, so if Modal's image has an older version, that could be the culprit.\n\nLet me check what version of httpx is actually installed in the Modal environment and whether the deployed app is still using the old code that had `with httpx.AsyncClient` instead of `async with httpx.AsyncClient`.","thinkingSignature":"3ebcf4d1c7518739ebad9e64cd1d808c0612376d8be5152d80c902e263bcde75"},{"type":"text","text":"The web UI loads but the API calls are broken. Let me check the current file state and fix the httpx issue:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_heokkwi6uq1i_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","offset":200,"limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73459,"output":342,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87793,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326080146}}
{"type":"message","id":"9241a8c8","parentId":"9ed1765d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:21:28.754Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_heokkwi6uq1i_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\r\n\r\n# ─── ASGI app ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n\r\n@app.function(image=_image)\r\n@modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama\")\r\ndef api():\r\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\r\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\r\n    import httpx\r\n\r\n    api = FastAPI()\r\n\r\n    @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\r\n    async def root():\r\n        return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\r\n\r\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\r\n    async def health():\r\n        try:\r\n            async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=5.0) as c:\r\n                r = await c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\r\n                return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"code\": r.status_code}\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)}\r\n\r\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\r\n    async def generate(req: dict):\r\n        start_ollama()\r\n        ensure_model()\r\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\r\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\r\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\r\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\r\n            r = await c.post(\r\n                f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\r\n                json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\r\n                      \"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": num_predict, \"stream\": False}\r\n            )\r\n            r.raise_for_status()\r\n            return r.json()\r\n\r\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\r\n    async def benchmarks():\r\n        start_ollama()\r\n        ensure_model()\r\n        BENCHMARK_PROMPTS = {\"gsm8k\": GSM8K, \"reasoning\": REASONING, \"code\": CODE}\r\n        results = {\"benchmarks\": [], \"timestamp\": time.time()}\r\n        for bench_name, prompts in BENCHMARK_PROMPTS.items():\r\n            bench_results, latencies = [], []\r\n\n[30 more lines in file. Use offset=250 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326088734}}
{"type":"message","id":"e512ffdc","parentId":"9241a8c8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:21:45.957Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file looks correct with `async with httpx.AsyncClient()`. But the deployed app is still returning the old error. Let me think about this...\n\nThe issue might be that Modal cached the old image when deploying with the charmap error, and the new image never got used. Let me check by looking at what image is being used.\n\nActually wait - the charmap error at the very end (`'charmap' codec can't encode character '\\u2713'`) is a Windows encoding issue when capturing the output of the deploy command. The actual Modal deploy might have succeeded but the error scrolled away. The image built (`im-jsWYt9HdmOsVx2Oc03PuUd`) and was deployed.\n\n\nBut the charmap encoding error is probably coming from Modal's local Python process trying to decode the server's output, not from Modal itself. The app is definitely deployed since the web UI loads, but the AsyncClient context manager error suggests the httpx version in the Modal image might be older and incompatible with how we're using it.\n\nActually, looking at the traceback more carefully - the error about context manager protocol support is happening on the server side within the ASGI app itself. The issue is that `httpx.AsyncClient` doesn't support the `async with` syntax in older versions. We're specifying `httpx` without a version constraint, so we might be getting an older release that has a different API. Let me check what version Modal's pip mirror actually serves.","thinkingSignature":"9e3959a466e9a74687dbc3b8bb1ff52e932726d65b51e689803a8bf84347caeb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9lbecd0aybng_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark; python -c \"import httpx; print(httpx.__version__)\" 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74279,"output":372,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88643,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326088757}}
{"type":"message","id":"a203a39d","parentId":"e512ffdc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:21:47.248Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9lbecd0aybng_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"0.28.1"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1217,"aggregated":"0.28.1","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326107226}}
{"type":"message","id":"78f02829","parentId":"a203a39d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:22:01.422Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"httpx 0.28.1 is installed locally. In httpx 0.28.1, `AsyncClient` should support `async with`. But the deployed version might be different. The issue is that Modal installs packages from a mirror during image build. The mirror might serve a different version.\n\nLet me pin httpx to a specific version to ensure consistency. Or better yet, let me use aiohttp instead of httpx for async HTTP calls, which is more standard in async Python web apps.\n\nActually, let me just use `requests` library (synchronous) instead since the endpoints are `async def` but the actual HTTP call doesn't need to be awaited at the top level. Wait no - in FastAPI, if you do blocking calls in async def, it blocks the event loop. We need async HTTP.\n \nThe real problem is that in httpx 0.28.1, `AsyncClient` works fine with `async with`, but there was a period around 0.26-0.27 where the API changed. Since Modal's mirror might be serving an older version, I should either pin httpx to `httpx>=0.28.0` explicitly in the pip_install call, or switch to using `aiohttp` which is more battle-tested in Modal's async environment.\n\nActually, let me reconsider the core issue. The Modal image already has Ollama installed and the app is deployed, so the `charmap` error was just from capturing the subprocess output. The real problem is that the FastAPI endpoints can't reach Ollama at `127.0.0.1:11434` because Ollama isn't running—the container starts the web app but Ollama never actually launches. I need to either start Ollama in the background when the container starts and keep it running, or find a way to launch it from within the FastAPI app itself.\n\nThe tricky part is that FastAPI runs async, so `subprocess.Popen` might not work reliably in that context. Let me think about whether there's a way to handle this within the image configuration itself, or if I need to restructure how the app initializes.\n\nActually, the cleanest fix is to set `exec` in the image definition to start Ollama when the container boots, before the web server runs. That way Ollama is already running when FastAPI needs it.","thinkingSignature":"ceee355ed937002dcf962c3851fb9d84f7daaa1cacd153b39721b4fddbd82b4b"},{"type":"text","text":"The issue is Ollama isn't starting in the container. Let me restructure — use Modal's `exec` to start Ollama at container boot:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9m3nw5zesta3_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74672,"output":555,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89219,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326107250}}
{"type":"message","id":"68057e23","parentId":"78f02829","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:22:01.476Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9m3nw5zesta3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nSPARK Ollama — FastAPI + Ollama + Eval Harness on Modal A100.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport subprocess\r\nimport time\r\nimport statistics\r\n\r\nimport modal\r\n\r\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\r\nOLLAMA_PORT = 11434\r\nMODEL_NAME = \"qwen2.5:7b\"\r\n\r\n# ─── Benchmark prompts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n\r\nGSM8K = [\r\n\r\n    \"There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the orchard today. When they finished, there were 21 trees in the orchard. How many trees did they plant today?\",\r\n    \"Leah has 6 apples and 4 oranges, and she eats 2 fruits. How many fruits does she have left?\",\r\n\r\n    \"A clown has 12 balloons. He gives away 5 to children. Later he buys 8 more balloons. How many balloons does he have now?\",\r\n    \"Tom has 5 baseball cards. He buys 3 more packs with 4 cards each. How many cards does he have total?\",\r\n\r\n    \"There are 3 pink flowers and 4 blue flowers in a vase. Sarah puts 2 more pink flowers in the vase. How many flowers are in the vase?\",\r\n]\r\n\r\nREASONING = [\r\n    \"If all Zeps are Mors, and some Mors are Leps, could some Zeps be Leps? Explain your reasoning.\",\r\n    \"Complete the pattern: 2, 6, 12, 20, 30, ?\",\r\n    \"What is heavier: a pound of feathers or a pound of bricks?\",\r\n    \"If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 widgets?\",\r\n    \"A farmer has 17 sheep. All but 9 die. How many are left?\",\r\n]\r\n\r\nCODE = [\r\n    \"Write a Python function to check if a string is a palindrome.\",\r\n    \"Write a Python function that returns the nth Fibonacci number using iteration.\",\r\n    \"Write a Python function to find the maximum element in a list without using max().\",\r\n]\r\n\r\n# ─── Ollama helpers (run in same container as ASGI app) ────────────────────\r\n\r\n_ollama_ready = [False]  # mutable flag\r\n\r\ndef start_ollama():\r\n    import httpx\r\n    try:\r\n        with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\r\n            r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\r\n            if r.status_code == 200:\r\n                _ollama_ready[0] = True\r\n                return\r\n    except Exception:\r\n        pass\r\n\r\n    print(\"Starting Ollama server...\")\r\n    subprocess.Popen(\r\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"serve\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", str(OLLAMA_PORT)],\r\n        stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL, stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\r\n    )\r\n    for _ in range(30):\r\n        try:\r\n            with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\r\n                r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\r\n                if r.status_code == 200:\r\n                    print(\"Ollama ready.\")\r\n                    _ollama_ready[0] = True\r\n                    return\r\n        except Exception:\r\n            pass\r\n        time.sleep(2)\r\n    raise RuntimeError(\"Ollama failed to start\")\r\n\r\n\r\ndef ensure_model():\r\n    result = subprocess.run([\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"list\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\r\n    if MODEL_NAME not in result.stdout:\r\n        print(f\"Pulling {MODEL_NAME} (this may take a few minutes)...\")\r\n        proc = subprocess.Popen([\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\r\n                                stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT, text=True)\r\n        for line in proc.stdout:\r\n            print(line, end=\"\", flush=True)\r\n        proc.wait()\r\n        print(\"Model ready.\")\r\n\r\n\r\n# ─── Image: Ollama + FastAPI deps ─────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n\r\n_image = (\r\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\r\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn[standard]\", \"httpx\")\r\n    .run_commands(\r\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd\",\r\n        \"curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\r\n    )\r\n)\r\n\r\n# ─── UI HTML ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n\r\nUI_HTML = \"\"\"<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"/><title>SPARK Eval</title><style>\r\n*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;background:#0f0f13;color:#e0e0e0;min-height:100vh}\r\n#root{padding:2rem;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}h1{color:#fff;margin-bottom:1.5rem}\r\n.card{background:#1a1a22;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border:1px solid #2a2a35}\r\n.card h2{color:#a0a0b0;font-size:.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:1rem}\r\nbutton{background:#6366f1;color:white;border:none;padding:.6rem 1.2rem;border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer;font-size:.9rem;font-weight:500}\r\nbutton:hover{background:#4f46e5}button:disabled{background:#3a3a4a;cursor:not-allowed}\r\n.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:.75rem}\r\n.stat-card{background:#14141c;border-radius:8px;padding:.9rem;border:1px solid #252530}\r\n.stat-card h3{color:#fff;margin-bottom:.4rem;font-size:.95rem}\r\n.s{color:#707080;font-size:.82rem;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:.2rem 0}\r\n.s span{color:#c0c0d0;font-family:monospace}\r\n.res{margin-top:.8rem;padding-top:.8rem;border-top:1px solid #252530}\r\n.q{color:#888898;font-size:.82rem;margin-bottom:.4rem}\r\n.a{color:#d0d0e0;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.5;background:#101018;padding:.7rem;border-radius:6px;white-space:pre-wrap}\r\n.lat{color:#6366f1;font-size:.75rem;margin-top:.3rem}\r\n.expander{cursor:pointer;padding:.4rem 0}.expander:hover{color:#fff}\r\n.header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-bottom:2rem;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.8rem}\r\n.badge{background:#252530;padding:.35rem .75rem;border-radius:6px;font-size:.78rem;color:#a0a0b0}\r\ninput{background:#14141c;border:1px solid #252530;color:#e0e0e0;padding:.6rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:.9rem;flex:1}\r\n.gen-form{display:flex;gap:.5rem;margin-bottom:.8rem}\r\n.status{font-size:.8rem}.ok{color:#22c55e}.err{color:#ef4444}\r\n</style></head><body><div id=\"root\"></div>\r\n<script type=\"module\">\r\nimport React,{useState,useEffect}from\"react\";import ReactDOM from\"react-dom/client\";import axios from\"axios\"\r\nconst API=\"\"\r\nconst App=()=>{\r\n  const[benchmarks,setBenchmarks]=useState(null)\r\n  const[loading,setLoading]=useState(false)\r\n  const[health,setHealth]=useState(null)\r\n  const[expanded,setExpanded]=useState({})\r\n  const[prompt,setPrompt]=useState(\"\")\r\n  const[genResult,setGenResult]=useState(null)\r\n  const[genning,setGening]=useState(false)\r\n  useEffect(()=>{(async()=>{try{const r=await axios.get(API+\"/health\");setHealth(r.data)}catch(e){setHealth({status:\"error\",error:e.message})}})()},[])\r\n  const run=async()=>{setLoading(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/benchmarks\");setBenchmarks(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setLoading(false)}\r\n  const send=async(e)=>{e.preventDefault();if(!prompt.trim())return;setGening(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/generate\",{prompt,temperature:.7,num_predict:300});setGenResult(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setGening(false)}\r\n  const toggle=(b,i)=>{const k=b+\"-\"+i;setExpanded(p=>({...p,[k]:!p[k]}))}\r\n  return React.createElement(\"div\",null,\r\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"header\"},\r\n      React.createElement(\"h1\",null,\"⚡ SPARK Eval\"),\r\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{style:{display:\"flex\",gap:\"1rem\",alignItems:\"center\"}},\r\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"badge\"},\"qwen2.5:7b\"),\r\n\r\n    React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"status \"+((health?.status===\"ok\")?\"ok\":\"err\")},health?.status===\"ok\"?\"● Online\":\"○ \"+(health?.error||\"Offline\")),\r\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{onClick:run,disabled:loading},loading?\"⏳ Running...\":\"Run Benchmarks\")\r\n      )\r\n    ),\r\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\r\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Chat\"),\r\n      React.createElement(\"form\",{className:\"gen-form\",onSubmit:send},\r\n\r\n    React.createElement(\"input\",{value:prompt,onChange:e=>setPrompt(e.target.value),placeholder:\"Ask the model...\"}),\r\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{type:\"submit\",disabled:genning},genning?\"...\":\"Send\")\r\n      ),\r\n      genResult&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},genResult.response)\r\n    ),\r\n    benchmarks&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\r\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\r\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Results — \"+new Date(benchmarks.timestamp*1000).toLocaleString()),\r\n        React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"grid\"},\r\n          benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"stat-card\"},\r\n            React.createElement(\"h3\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()),\r\n\r\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Prompts\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.num_prompts)),\r\n\r\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Avg Latency\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.avg_latency_s+\"s\")),\r\n\r\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Total Time\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.total_time_s+\"s\"))\r\n          ))\r\n        )\r\n      ),\r\n      benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"card\"},\r\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()+\" — Responses\"),\r\n        b.results.map((r,i)=>{\r\n          const k=b.name+\"-\"+i\r\n          return React.createElement(\"div\",{key:i,className:\"res\"},\r\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"expander\",onClick:()=>toggle(b.name,i)},\r\n              React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"q\"},\"Q: \"+r.prompt.slice(0,85)+(r.prompt.length>85?\"...\":\"\")),\r\n\r\n    React.createElement(\"span\",{style:{color:\"#6366f1\",fontSize:\".75rem\",marginLeft:\".5rem\"}},expanded[k]?\"▲\":\"▼\")\r\n            ),\r\n            expanded[k]&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\r\n              React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},\"A: \"+r.response),\r\n              React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"lat\"},r.latency_s+\"s\")\r\n            )\r\n          )\r\n        })\r\n      ))\r\n    ),\r\n    !benchmarks&&!loading&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\r\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Ready\"),\r\n\r\n    React.createElement(\"p\",{style:{color:\"#707080\",fontSize:\".88rem\"}},'Click \"Run Benchmarks\" to evaluate GSM8K math, reasoning, and code tasks.')\r\n    )\r\n  )\r\n}\r\nReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById(\"root\")).render(React.createElement(App))\r\n</script></body></html>\"\"\"\r\n\r\n\r\n# ─── ASGI app ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n\r\n@app.function(image=_image)\r\n@modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama\")\r\ndef api():\r\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\r\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\r\n    import httpx\r\n\r\n    api = FastAPI()\r\n\r\n    @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\r\n    async def root():\r\n        return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\r\n\r\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\r\n    async def health():\r\n        try:\r\n            async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=5.0) as c:\r\n                r = await c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\r\n                return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"code\": r.status_code}\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)}\r\n\r\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\r\n    async def generate(req: dict):\r\n        start_ollama()\r\n        ensure_model()\r\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\r\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\r\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\r\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\r\n            r = await c.post(\r\n                f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\r\n                json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\r\n                      \"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": num_predict, \"stream\": False}\r\n            )\r\n            r.raise_for_status()\r\n            return r.json()\r\n\r\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\r\n    async def benchmarks():\r\n        start_ollama()\r\n        ensure_model()\r\n        BENCHMARK_PROMPTS = {\"gsm8k\": GSM8K, \"reasoning\": REASONING, \"code\": CODE}\r\n        results = {\"benchmarks\": [], \"timestamp\": time.time()}\r\n        for bench_name, prompts in BENCHMARK_PROMPTS.items():\r\n            bench_results, latencies = [], []\r\n            for prompt in prompts:\r\n                t0 = time.perf_counter()\r\n                try:\r\n                    async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\r\n                        r = await c.post(\r\n                            f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\r\n                            json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\r\n                                  \"temperature\": 0.7, \"num_predict\": 300, \"stream\": False}\r\n                        )\r\n                        r.raise_for_status()\r\n                        response_text = r.json().get(\"response\", \"\")\r\n                except Exception as e:\r\n                    response_text = f\"ERROR: {str(e)}\"\r\n                latency = time.perf_counter() - t0\r\n                latencies.append(latency)\r\n                bench_results.append({\"prompt\": prompt, \"response\": response_text, \"latency_s\": round(latency, 3)})\r\n            results[\"benchmarks\"].append({\r\n                \"name\": bench_name, \"num_prompts\": len(prompts),\r\n                \"avg_latency_s\": round(statistics.mean(latencies), 3),\r\n                \"total_time_s\": round(sum(latencies), 3), \"results\": bench_results,\r\n            })\r\n        return results\r\n\r\n    return api\r\n\r\n\r\n@app.local_entrypoint()\r\ndef main():\r\n    print(\"SPARK deployed — check Modal dashboard for URL.\")\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326121453}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0afa422","parentId":"68057e23","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:23:09.007Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `start_ollama()` and `ensure_model()` are being called inside FastAPI request handlers, but they use `subprocess.Popen` which doesn't work reliably in Modal's async environment. Also, the model pulling is synchronous and blocking, which would time out the request.\n\nThe fundamental problem: I can't pull a 5GB model inside a request handler that has a 60s timeout. I need to pre-pull the model at startup.\n\nLet me restructure:\n1. Use `exec` to start Ollama at container startup (runs in background)\n2. Use a `run_function` to pre-pull the model at deploy time (not at request time)\n\n\n3. Have the FastAPI handlers just make HTTP requests to localhost:11434\n\nFor Modal, I should set up a background function that starts Ollama when the container starts, then the ASGI app can just query whether Ollama is ready rather than trying to manage it per-request.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach is to use a `modal.BackgroundTask` or just run Ollama as a subprocess that gets started once when the container boots. I'm thinking about using `container.lifecycle` to handle startup and shutdown, though I'm not entirely sure if Modal's API supports that directly. Alternatively, I could run a background function with `wait=False` during app initialization to pull the model, then start the server separately.\n\nLet me try combining `setup` and `exec` in the image definition—the setup function pulls the model once at deploy time, and exec starts Ollama as a background daemon that stays running.","thinkingSignature":"2f1ec3d4d28e1e71d2b2c64b054449e0194098a08ec05beeae869aafceb69ab4"},{"type":"text","text":"The real issue: pulling a 5GB model inside request handlers times out. Let me restructure properly — pull model at deploy time, start Ollama as a background process at container start:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m6xa53onyy3j_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","content":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama — FastAPI + Ollama + Eval Harness on Modal A100.\nOllama runs as a background service, model pulled once at deploy.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport time\nimport statistics\nimport threading\nimport os\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\nOLLAMA_PORT = 11434\nMODEL_NAME = \"qwen2.5:7b\"\n\n# ─── Benchmark prompts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nGSM8K = [\n    \"There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the orchard today. When they finished, there were 21 trees in the orchard. How many trees did they plant today?\",\n    \"Leah has 6 apples and 4 oranges, and she eats 2 fruits. How many fruits does she have left?\",\n    \"A clown has 12 balloons. He gives away 5 to children. Later he buys 8 more balloons. How many balloons does he have now?\",\n    \"Tom has 5 baseball cards. He buys 3 more packs with 4 cards each. How many cards does he have total?\",\n    \"There are 3 pink flowers and 4 blue flowers in a vase. Sarah puts 2 more pink flowers in the vase. How many flowers are in the vase?\",\n]\n\nREASONING = [\n    \"If all Zeps are Mors, and some Mors are Leps, could some Zeps be Leps? Explain your reasoning.\",\n    \"Complete the pattern: 2, 6, 12, 20, 30, ?\",\n    \"What is heavier: a pound of feathers or a pound of bricks?\",\n    \"If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 widgets?\",\n    \"A farmer has 17 sheep. All but 9 die. How many are left?\",\n]\n\nCODE = [\n    \"Write a Python function to check if a string is a palindrome.\",\n    \"Write a Python function that returns the nth Fibonacci number using iteration.\",\n    \"Write a Python function to find the maximum element in a list without using max().\",\n]\n\n\n# ─── Image with Ollama + deps ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn[standard]\", \"httpx>=0.28.0\")\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd\",\n        \"curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )\n)\n\n\n# ─── Container lifecycle: start Ollama + pull model ───────────────────────────\n\n@app.function(image=_image, timeout=900, container_idle_timeout=300)\ndef setup_ollama():\n    \"\"\"Pull model and start Ollama. Runs once at deploy.\"\"\"\n    import httpx\n    import subprocess\n    import time\n    import os\n\n    # Start Ollama in background\n    print(\"Starting Ollama server in background...\")\n    with open(\"/tmp/ollama.log\", \"w\") as log:\n        proc = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"serve\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", str(OLLAMA_PORT)],\n            stdout=log, stderr=log,\n        )\n\n    # Wait for Ollama API to come up\n    print(\"Waiting for Ollama API...\")\n    for i in range(60):\n        try:\n            with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\n                r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                if r.status_code == 200:\n                    print(\"Ollama API is up!\")\n                    break\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n        time.sleep(2)\n    else:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"Ollama API failed to start\")\n\n    # Check if model already present\n    result = subprocess.run(\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"list\"],\n        capture_output=True, text=True,\n    )\n    if MODEL_NAME not in result.stdout:\n        print(f\"Pulling {MODEL_NAME} (first time, may take a few minutes)...\")\n        pull_proc = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\n            stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT, text=True,\n        )\n        for line in pull_proc.stdout:\n            print(line, end=\"\", flush=True)\n        pull_proc.wait()\n        if pull_proc.returncode != 0:\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Model pull failed for {MODEL_NAME}\")\n        print(\"Model ready!\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"Model {MODEL_NAME} already present.\")\n\n    print(\"Setup complete. Ollama running on port\", OLLAMA_PORT)\n    print(f\"APP URL will be: https://{os.environ.get('MODAL_MAIN_APP', 'spark-ollama')}.modal.run\")\n    return {\"status\": \"ready\", \"model\": MODEL_NAME}\n\n\n# ─── UI HTML ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nUI_HTML = \"\"\"<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"/><title>SPARK Eval</title><style>\n*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;background:#0f0f13;color:#e0e0e0;min-height:100vh}\n#root{padding:2rem;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}h1{color:#fff;margin-bottom:1.5rem}\n.card{background:#1a1a22;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border:1px solid #2a2a35}\n.card h2{color:#a0a0b0;font-size:.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:1rem}\nbutton{background:#6366f1;color:white;border:none;padding:.6rem 1.2rem;border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer;font-size:.9rem;font-weight:500}\nbutton:hover{background:#4f46e5}button:disabled{background:#3a3a4a;cursor:not-allowed}\n.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:.75rem}\n.stat-card{background:#14141c;border-radius:8px;padding:.9rem;border:1px solid #252530}\n.stat-card h3{color:#fff;margin-bottom:.4rem;font-size:.95rem}\n.s{color:#707080;font-size:.82rem;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:.2rem 0}\n.s span{color:#c0c0d0;font-family:monospace}\n.res{margin-top:.8rem;padding-top:.8rem;border-top:1px solid #252530}\n.q{color:#888898;font-size:.82rem;margin-bottom:.4rem}\n.a{color:#d0d0e0;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.5;background:#101018;padding:.7rem;border-radius:6px;white-space:pre-wrap}\n.lat{color:#6366f1;font-size:.75rem;margin-top:.3rem}\n.expander{cursor:pointer;padding:.4rem 0}.expander:hover{color:#fff}\n.header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-bottom:2rem;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.8rem}\n.badge{background:#252530;padding:.35rem .75rem;border-radius:6px;font-size:.78rem;color:#a0a0b0}\ninput{background:#14141c;border:1px solid #252530;color:#e0e0e0;padding:.6rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:.9rem;flex:1}\n.gen-form{display:flex;gap:.5rem;margin-bottom:.8rem}\n.status{font-size:.8rem}.ok{color:#22c55e}.err{color:#ef4444}\n</style></head><body><div id=\"root\"></div>\n<script type=\"module\">\nimport React,{useState,useEffect}from\"react\";import ReactDOM from\"react-dom/client\";import axios from\"axios\"\nconst API=\"\"\nconst App=()=>{\n  const[benchmarks,setBenchmarks]=useState(null)\n  const[loading,setLoading]=useState(false)\n  const[health,setHealth]=useState(null)\n  const[expanded,setExpanded]=useState({})\n  const[prompt,setPrompt]=useState(\"\")\n  const[genResult,setGenResult]=useState(null)\n  const[genning,setGening]=useState(false)\n  useEffect(()=>{(async()=>{try{const r=await axios.get(API+\"/health\");setHealth(r.data)}catch(e){setHealth({status:\"error\",error:e.message})}})()},[])\n  const run=async()=>{setLoading(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/benchmarks\");setBenchmarks(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setLoading(false)}\n  const send=async(e)=>{e.preventDefault();if(!prompt.trim())return;setGening(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/generate\",{prompt,temperature:.7,num_predict:300});setGenResult(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setGening(false)}\n  const toggle=(b,i)=>{const k=b+\"-\"+i;setExpanded(p=>({...p,[k]:!p[k]}))}\n  return React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"header\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h1\",null,\"SPARK Eval\"),\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{style:{display:\"flex\",gap:\"1rem\",alignItems:\"center\"}},\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"badge\"},\"qwen2.5:7b\"),\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"status \"+((health?.status===\"ok\")?\"ok\":\"err\")},health?.status===\"ok\"?\"Online\":\"Offline: \"+(health?.error||\"\")),\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{onClick:run,disabled:loading},loading?\"Running...\":\"Run Benchmarks\")\n      )\n    ),\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Chat\"),\n      React.createElement(\"form\",{className:\"gen-form\",onSubmit:send},\n        React.createElement(\"input\",{value:prompt,onChange:e=>setPrompt(e.target.value),placeholder:\"Ask the model...\"}),\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{type:\"submit\",disabled:genning},genning?\"...\":\"Send\")\n      ),\n      genResult&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},genResult.response)\n    ),\n    benchmarks&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Results\"),\n        React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"grid\"},\n          benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"stat-card\"},\n            React.createElement(\"h3\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Prompts\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.num_prompts)),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Avg Latency\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.avg_latency_s+\"s\")),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Total Time\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.total_time_s+\"s\"))\n          ))\n        )\n      ),\n      benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"card\"},\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()+\" Responses\"),\n        b.results.map((r,i)=>{\n          const k=b.name+\"-\"+i\n          return React.createElement(\"div\",{key:i,className:\"res\"},\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"expander\",onClick:()=>toggle(b.name,i)},\n              React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"q\"},\"Q: \"+r.prompt.slice(0,85)+(r.prompt.length>85?\"...\":\"\")),\n              React.createElement(\"span\",{style:{color:\"#6366f1\",fontSize:\".75rem\",marginLeft:\".5rem\"}},expanded[k]?\"▲\":\"▼\")\n            ),\n            expanded[k]&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n              React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},\"A: \"+r.response),\n              React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"lat\"},r.latency_s+\"s\")\n            )\n          )\n        })\n      ))\n    ),\n    !benchmarks&&!loading&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Ready\"),\n      React.createElement(\"p\",{style:{color:\"#707080\",fontSize:\".88rem\"}},'Click \"Run Benchmarks\" to evaluate the model.')\n    )\n  )\n}\nReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById(\"root\")).render(React.createElement(App))\n</script></body></html>\"\"\"\n\n\n# ─── Web server (separate from Ollama setup) ─────────────────────────────────\n\n# The web server uses the SAME image but is a different container.\n# It needs to find Ollama at the host IP, not localhost.\n# We get the host IP from the OLLAMA_HOST env var set by Modal.\n\n_web_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn[standard]\", \"httpx>=0.28.0\")\n)\n\n\n@app.function(image=_web_image, timeout=3600, scaledown_window=600)\n@modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama\", wait_for_app=False)\ndef web_server():\n    \"\"\"FastAPI web server — talks to Ollama via OLLAMA_HOST env var.\"\"\"\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n    import httpx\n    import os\n\n    api = FastAPI()\n    ollama_host = os.environ.get(\"OLLAMA_HOST\", f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}\")\n    model = os.environ.get(\"OLLAMA_MODEL\", MODEL_NAME)\n\n    @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\n    async def root():\n        return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        try:\n            async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=5.0) as c:\n                r = await c.get(f\"{ollama_host}/\")\n                return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"code\": r.status_code, \"host\": ollama_host}\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e), \"host\": ollama_host}\n\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\n    async def generate(req: dict):\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n            r = await c.post(\n                f\"{ollama_host}/api/generate\",\n                json={\"model\": model, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                      \"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": num_predict, \"stream\": False}\n            )\n            r.raise_for_status()\n            return r.json()\n\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\n    async def benchmarks():\n        BENCHMARK_PROMPTS = {\"gsm8k\": GSM8K, \"reasoning\": REASONING, \"code\": CODE}\n        results = {\"benchmarks\": [], \"timestamp\": time.time()}\n        for bench_name, prompts in BENCHMARK_PROMPTS.items():\n            bench_results, latencies = [], []\n            for prompt in prompts:\n                t0 = time.perf_counter()\n                try:\n                    async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n                        r = await c.post(\n                            f\"{ollama_host}/api/generate\",\n                            json={\"model\": model, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                                  \"temperature\": 0.7, \"num_predict\": 300, \"stream\": False}\n                        )\n                        r.raise_for_status()\n                        response_text = r.json().get(\"response\", \"\")\n                except Exception as e:\n                    response_text = f\"ERROR: {str(e)}\"\n                latency = time.perf_counter() - t0\n                latencies.append(latency)\n                bench_results.append({\"prompt\": prompt, \"response\": response_text, \"latency_s\": round(latency, 3)})\n            results[\"benchmarks\"].append({\n                \"name\": bench_name, \"num_prompts\": len(prompts),\n                \"avg_latency_s\": round(statistics.mean(latencies), 3),\n                \"total_time_s\": round(sum(latencies), 3), \"results\": bench_results,\n            })\n        return results\n\n    return api\n\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef main():\n    print(\"Two-step deploy:\")\n    print(\"1. Run: modal run spark/modal_spark.py::setup_ollama  (one-time model pull + Ollama start)\")\n    print(\"2. Run: modal deploy spark/modal_spark.py              (deploy web server)\")\n    print(\"\")\n    print(\"Or just 'modal deploy spark/modal_spark.py' — setup_ollama runs automatically\")\n    result = setup_ollama.remote()\n    print(\"Setup result:\", result)\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":78897,"output":4276,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97165,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326121478}}
{"type":"message","id":"051ca442","parentId":"d0afa422","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:23:09.127Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_m6xa53onyy3j_1","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 14490 bytes to C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326189094}}
{"type":"message","id":"10669bcc","parentId":"051ca442","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:24:18.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, this architecture is getting complicated. The issue is that I'm trying to run two different things (Ollama server + FastAPI web server) in the same app, but they're separate containers. This means:\n1. `setup_ollama` runs in one container, starts Ollama, pulls model\n2. `web_server` runs in a DIFFERENT container and needs to connect to Ollama at some host IP\n\nBut Modal containers can't easily talk to each other by IP. They're on the same network but the IP isn't predictable. I need a different approach.\n\n**Better architecture: Single container, fork/exec Ollama inside the same container as the web server.**\n\n\nI should leverage Modal's `web_server` with background functions to handle this - the main container can fork Ollama as a subprocess and keep it running, while the web server makes requests to localhost where Ollama is already listening. to handle long-running processes\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to just put everything in one container. The `setup_ollama` runs at deploy time, pulling the model, and the `web_server` runs as the ASGI app. Since they're both in the same container, I don't need separate networking.\n\nBut wait - `setup_ollama` is a `@modal.function()` which runs in its own container! And `web_server` is a `@modal.asgi_app()` which runs in yet another container!\n\nSo I have two separate containers that can't communicate over localhost. The real issue is that functions and web apps in Modal don't share the same filesystem or process space, so I can't have one pull the model and have the other access it.\n\nI could use a shared Volume, but Ollama stores models in `~/.ollama` by default, which would be per-container. The solution is to configure Ollama with `OLLAMA_MODELS` pointing to a Volume mount, then both containers can access the same model files. Alternatively, I could make the web app itself responsible for starting Ollama on first request rather than relying on a separate setup function.\n\nBut starting a long-running subprocess like Ollama inside a request handler is problematic. I think the cleanest approach is to use a `modal.BackgroundTask` that starts Ollama once when the container starts, or leverage Modal's `exec` to run a command before the container begins handling requests.\n\nActually, wait—I'm overcomplicating this. The real issue is that Modal's sandboxed environment might not support GPU access the way I'm thinking. Let me step back: when `setup_ollama` runs in a container and starts Ollama in the background, then `web_server` gets a separate container, they can't share localhost. But if I structure this as a single app with one container type that handles both Ollama startup and web serving, it might work differently.\n\nThe problem is that `asgi_app` and regular `@function()` decorated endpoints run in different containers by default, so they can't see each other's processes. I could try using `wait_for_app=False` to keep them in the same container, or look into Modal's `web_endpoint` with background tasks, or maybe just spin up Ollama on a GPU-enabled function and have the web app call it directly.\n\nActually, the simplest approach might be to just run everything in the local entrypoint instead of trying to distribute it across Modal's infrastructure.\n\nBut that's not scalable. Let me step back and think about what I actually need: an A100 for Ollama, plus a web interface. The cleanest path forward is probably to keep Ollama running as a long-lived service in one container and have the web app send requests to it, rather than trying to start it on-demand. Or I could use Modal's built-in model serving features instead of running Ollama manually. Actually, let me just try the simplest possible architecture: deploy the web server as-is and see if I can at least get the health check working by configuring the `OLLAMA_HOST` environment variable to point to the right place.","thinkingSignature":"c92a878d2cfbb2d91371dacd5727e13a71f88c80ab5aed755da099943c1f772d"},{"type":"text","text":"Actually, let me step back and try the simplest possible approach — use Modal's web_server with environment variable for the Ollama host, and a BackgroundTask to start Ollama in the same container:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_shr5hwtr6hh1_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","content":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama — FastAPI + Ollama + Eval Harness on Modal A100.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport time\nimport statistics\nimport os\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\nOLLAMA_PORT = 11434\nMODEL_NAME = \"qwen2.5:7b\"\n\n# ─── Benchmark prompts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nGSM8K = [\n    \"There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the orchard today. When they finished, there were 21 trees in the orchard. How many trees did they plant today?\",\n    \"Leah has 6 apples and 4 oranges, and she eats 2 fruits. How many fruits does she have left?\",\n    \"A clown has 12 balloons. He gives away 5 to children. Later he buys 8 more balloons. How many balloons does he have now?\",\n    \"Tom has 5 baseball cards. He buys 3 more packs with 4 cards each. How many cards does he have total?\",\n    \"There are 3 pink flowers and 4 blue flowers in a vase. Sarah puts 2 more pink flowers in the vase. How many flowers are in the vase?\",\n]\n\nREASONING = [\n    \"If all Zeps are Mors, and some Mors are Leps, could some Zeps be Leps? Explain your reasoning.\",\n    \"Complete the pattern: 2, 6, 12, 20, 30, ?\",\n    \"What is heavier: a pound of feathers or a pound of bricks?\",\n    \"If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 widgets?\",\n    \"A farmer has 17 sheep. All but 9 die. How many are left?\",\n]\n\nCODE = [\n    \"Write a Python function to check if a string is a palindrome.\",\n    \"Write a Python function that returns the nth Fibonacci number using iteration.\",\n    \"Write a Python function to find the maximum element in a list without using max().\",\n]\n\n# ─── Image ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn[standard]\", \"httpx>=0.28.0\")\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd\",\n        \"curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )\n)\n\n# ─── UI HTML ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nUI_HTML = \"\"\"<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"/><title>SPARK Eval</title><style>\n*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;background:#0f0f13;color:#e0e0e0;min-height:100vh}\n#root{padding:2rem;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}h1{color:#fff;margin-bottom:1.5rem}\n.card{background:#1a1a22;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border:1px solid #2a2a35}\n.card h2{color:#a0a0b0;font-size:.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:1rem}\nbutton{background:#6366f1;color:white;border:none;padding:.6rem 1.2rem;border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer;font-size:.9rem;font-weight:500}\nbutton:hover{background:#4f46e5}button:disabled{background:#3a3a4a;cursor:not-allowed}\n.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:.75rem}\n.stat-card{background:#14141c;border-radius:8px;padding:.9rem;border:1px solid #252530}\n.stat-card h3{color:#fff;margin-bottom:.4rem;font-size:.95rem}\n.s{color:#707080;font-size:.82rem;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:.2rem 0}\n.s span{color:#c0c0d0;font-family:monospace}\n.res{margin-top:.8rem;padding-top:.8rem;border-top:1px solid #252530}\n.q{color:#888898;font-size:.82rem;margin-bottom:.4rem}\n.a{color:#d0d0e0;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.5;background:#101018;padding:.7rem;border-radius:6px;white-space:pre-wrap}\n.lat{color:#6366f1;font-size:.75rem;margin-top:.3rem}\n.expander{cursor:pointer;padding:.4rem 0}.expander:hover{color:#fff}\n.header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-bottom:2rem;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.8rem}\n.badge{background:#252530;padding:.35rem .75rem;border-radius:6px;font-size:.78rem;color:#a0a0b0}\ninput{background:#14141c;border:1px solid #252530;color:#e0e0e0;padding:.6rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:.9rem;flex:1}\n.gen-form{display:flex;gap:.5rem;margin-bottom:.8rem}\n.status{font-size:.8rem}.ok{color:#22c55e}.err{color:#ef4444}\n</style></head><body><div id=\"root\"></div>\n<script type=\"module\">\nimport React,{useState,useEffect}from\"react\";import ReactDOM from\"react-dom/client\";import axios from\"axios\"\nconst API=\"\"\nconst App=()=>{\n  const[benchmarks,setBenchmarks]=useState(null)\n  const[loading,setLoading]=useState(false)\n  const[health,setHealth]=useState(null)\n  const[expanded,setExpanded]=useState({})\n  const[prompt,setPrompt]=useState(\"\")\n  const[genResult,setGenResult]=useState(null)\n  const[genning,setGening]=useState(false)\n  useEffect(()=>{(async()=>{try{const r=await axios.get(API+\"/health\");setHealth(r.data)}catch(e){setHealth({status:\"error\",error:e.message})}})()},[])\n  const run=async()=>{setLoading(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/benchmarks\");setBenchmarks(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setLoading(false)}\n  const send=async(e)=>{e.preventDefault();if(!prompt.trim())return;setGening(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/generate\",{prompt,temperature:.7,num_predict:300});setGenResult(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setGening(false)}\n  const toggle=(b,i)=>{const k=b+\"-\"+i;setExpanded(p=>({...p,[k]:!p[k]}))}\n  return React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"header\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h1\",null,\"SPARK Eval\"),\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{style:{display:\"flex\",gap:\"1rem\",alignItems:\"center\"}},\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"badge\"},\"qwen2.5:7b\"),\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"status \"+((health?.status===\"ok\")?\"ok\":\"err\")},health?.status===\"ok\"?\"Online\":\"Offline\"),\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{onClick:run,disabled:loading},loading?\"Running...\":\"Run Benchmarks\")\n      )\n    ),\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Chat\"),\n      React.createElement(\"form\",{className:\"gen-form\",onSubmit:send},\n        React.createElement(\"input\",{value:prompt,onChange:e=>setPrompt(e.target.value),placeholder:\"Ask the model...\"}),\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{type:\"submit\",disabled:genning},genning?\"...\":\"Send\")\n      ),\n      genResult&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},genResult.response)\n    ),\n    benchmarks&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Results\"),\n        React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"grid\"},\n          benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"stat-card\"},\n            React.createElement(\"h3\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Prompts\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.num_prompts)),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Avg Latency\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.avg_latency_s+\"s\")),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Total Time\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.total_time_s+\"s\"))\n          ))\n        )\n      ),\n      benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"card\"},\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()+\" Responses\"),\n        b.results.map((r,i)=>{\n          const k=b.name+\"-\"+i\n          return React.createElement(\"div\",{key:i,className:\"res\"},\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"expander\",onClick:()=>toggle(b.name,i)},\n              React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"q\"},\"Q: \"+r.prompt.slice(0,85)+(r.prompt.length>85?\"...\":\"\")),\n              React.createElement(\"span\",{style:{color:\"#6366f1\",fontSize:\".75rem\",marginLeft:\".5rem\"}},expanded[k]?\"▲\":\"▼\")\n            ),\n            expanded[k]&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n              React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},\"A: \"+r.response),\n              React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"lat\"},r.latency_s+\"s\")\n            )\n          )\n        })\n      ))\n    ),\n    !benchmarks&&!loading&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Ready\"),\n      React.createElement(\"p\",{style:{color:\"#707080\",fontSize:\".88rem\"}},'Click \"Run Benchmarks\" to evaluate the model.')\n    )\n  )\n}\nReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById(\"root\")).render(React.createElement(App))\n</script></body></html>\"\"\"\n\n\n# ─── Background task: start Ollama in this container ─────────────────────────\n\n@app.function(image=_image, timeout=3600, container_idle_timeout=300)\n@modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama\")\ndef api():\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n    import httpx\n    import asyncio\n\n    api = FastAPI()\n\n    # Lazy-start Ollama + pull model on first request\n    _ollama_started = {\"done\": False}\n\n    async def ensure_ollama():\n        if _ollama_started[\"done\"]:\n            return\n        import subprocess\n        import os\n\n        # Check if already running\n        try:\n            async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=5.0) as c:\n                r = await c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                if r.status_code == 200:\n                    _ollama_started[\"done\"] = True\n                    return\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n\n        # Start Ollama in background thread (non-blocking for async)\n        print(\"Starting Ollama...\")\n        loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()\n        await loop.run_in_executor(None, _start_ollama_sync)\n        _ollama_started[\"done\"] = True\n        print(\"Ollama started.\")\n\n    def _start_ollama_sync():\n        import subprocess\n        # Start Ollama server\n        proc = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"serve\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", str(OLLAMA_PORT)],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL, stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n        )\n        # Wait for it to be ready\n        import httpx\n        for _ in range(30):\n            try:\n                with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\n                    r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                    if r.status_code == 200:\n                        break\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n            import time; time.sleep(2)\n        # Pull model if needed\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"list\"], capture_output=True, text=True,\n        )\n        if MODEL_NAME not in result.stdout:\n            print(f\"Pulling {MODEL_NAME}...\")\n            pull = subprocess.Popen(\n                [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\n                stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT, text=True,\n            )\n            for line in pull.stdout:\n                print(line.decode(errors=\"replace\") if isinstance(line, bytes) else line, end=\"\", flush=True)\n            pull.wait()\n            print(\"Model ready.\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Model {MODEL_NAME} already present.\")\n\n    @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\n    async def root():\n        return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        await ensure_ollama()\n        try:\n            async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=5.0) as c:\n                r = await c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"code\": r.status_code}\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)}\n\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\n    async def generate(req: dict):\n        await ensure_ollama()\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n            r = await c.post(\n                f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                      \"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": num_predict, \"stream\": False}\n            )\n            r.raise_for_status()\n            return r.json()\n\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\n    async def benchmarks():\n        await ensure_ollama()\n        BENCHMARK_PROMPTS = {\"gsm8k\": GSM8K, \"reasoning\": REASONING, \"code\": CODE}\n        results = {\"benchmarks\": [], \"timestamp\": time.time()}\n        for bench_name, prompts in BENCHMARK_PROMPTS.items():\n            bench_results, latencies = [], []\n            for prompt in prompts:\n                t0 = time.perf_counter()\n                try:\n                    async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n                        r = await c.post(\n                            f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                            json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                                  \"temperature\": 0.7, \"num_predict\": 300, \"stream\": False}\n                        )\n                        r.raise_for_status()\n                        response_text = r.json().get(\"response\", \"\")\n                except Exception as e:\n                    response_text = f\"ERROR: {str(e)}\"\n                latency = time.perf_counter() - t0\n                latencies.append(latency)\n                bench_results.append({\"prompt\": prompt, \"response\": response_text, \"latency_s\": round(latency, 3)})\n            results[\"benchmarks\"].append({\n                \"name\": bench_name, \"num_prompts\": len(prompts),\n                \"avg_latency_s\": round(statistics.mean(latencies), 3),\n                \"total_time_s\": round(sum(latencies), 3), \"results\": bench_results,\n            })\n        return results\n\n    return api\n\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef main():\n    print(\"Deploying SPARK to Modal...\")\n    print(\"UI URL will be shown after deployment.\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":83214,"output":4541,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101747,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326189130}}
