{"type":"message","id":"0b975bfd","parentId":"06e09e27","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:24:45.405Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The charmap error is happening again. This is a Windows encoding issue when Modal tries to capture the output of the Ollama install script. The install script is running fine (we can see it succeeded previously), but the Windows Python process that's running modal CLI can't encode the checkmark character in the output.The issue is that the subprocess that runs `modal deploy` is a Windows process using a console encoding that can't handle the UTF-8 output from the Linux container. The actual deploy might succeed, but the local process crashes when trying to print the output.\n\nLet me check if the app was actually deployed despite the error by checking the app list.","thinkingSignature":"f8c8d979b447cef8bc0767b159a2686c7646b20f8569d7610ecc2c3b22e20f87"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7m1z94honnu2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"modal app list 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":90144,"output":171,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104307,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326270660}}
