{"type":"message","id":"37102f49","parentId":"d9ce2a98","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:24:57.484Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The app is still showing the old deployed version from yesterday (2026-03-23 10:41). The new deployment failed, so the old version is still running.\n\nThe charmap issue is a Windows encoding problem. When Modal's Python CLI runs on Windows, it captures the output of the container's commands and tries to print them to the Windows console. The console's default encoding (cp1252 or similar) can't encode UTF-8 characters like ✓.\n\nThere are a few ways to fix this:\n1. Set the environment variable `PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8` before running modal\n2. Use `chcp 65001` (UTF-8 code page) in Windows\n\n\n3. Modify the code to avoid non-ASCII characters in output\n\nThe real issue is that the subprocess output from the Linux container contains UTF-8 characters (like ✓ from Ollama's install script), and when Modal's Python tries to display this on a Windows console with a limited encoding, it crashes. I should try setting `PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8` to handle the UTF-8 output properly.\n\nLet me test whether setting that environment variable resolves the deploy issue.","thinkingSignature":"3259dfbdbf3114f197a297ab05f5af9e766f7d08b9926a4faa150e092c57c084"},{"type":"text","text":"The deploy failed but the old app is still live. The `charmap` error is a Windows encoding issue when capturing Linux container output. Let me fix the encoding:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2t0lyxqdulbv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark; $env:PYTHONIOENCODING=\"utf-8\"; $env:PYTHONUTF8=\"1\"; modal deploy modal_spark.py 2>&1","timeout":600}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":90466,"output":360,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104818,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}}