{"type":"message","id":"6a9802d9","parentId":"57d1c4a7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:28:10.205Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The HTML page loads fine! The web server is working. But `/health` fails with \"All connection attempts failed\". This means the FastAPI endpoint is trying to connect to `http://127.0.0.1:11434` (Ollama) but failing because Ollama isn't running.\n\nThe `_start_ollama_bg()` function should have been triggered by the first health request... but wait. In Modal's ASGI app, each container might handle multiple requests concurrently, and the module-level `_ollama_state` might not be shared properly. Also, the `run_in_executor` call might not be working as expected.\n\nBut more importantly - the health endpoint returns immediately with the current state and *also* triggers the background start. \n\nAh, I see the issue now - the health endpoint checks if `_ollama_state[\"status\"]` is \"unknown\" to trigger startup, but when the endpoint returns the state as JSON in the response, the background thread is actually calling `_start_ollama_bg()` which tries to start Ollama. So the health response correctly shows \"unknown\" status, but the real problem is that Ollama itself isn't running at all.\n\nI'm realizing that `_ollama_state` might not be persisting across requests since Modal reimports the module, and even if it did, `run_in_executor` wouldn't properly propagate back to the caller. But honestly, I don't even know if Ollama can run on Modal's infrastructure in the first place - their sandbox might have limitations that prevent it from working properly.\n\nLet me check Modal's documentation to understand what's actually supported. Maybe I should try running a simple test to see if subprocess commands work at all in this environment, or just look for an existing Modal + Ollama integration example rather than trying to force something that might not be compatible.","thinkingSignature":"fac1416d92907af6a5507620f77e8f1c80911bc1d84310b3452e655f424db9ea"},{"type":"text","text":"The web server works fine — but Ollama isn't starting. Let me check if Ollama binary works at all in this environment:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aslp1ngjlrve_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"SSH to Modal or run a simple test: modal run a quick function that checks if /usr/local/bin/ollama exists and can show its version. Then try to start it and see if it works. File: C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py. Just check if ollama binary is there and its version.","runtime":"subagent","runTimeoutSeconds":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":116869,"output":524,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131385,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326475268}}
