{"type":"message","id":"0d93cca8","parentId":"0c19c0d6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:29:50.910Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but ASGI apps can't have GPU directly. The `gpu` parameter on `@app.function()` is for regular functions. For ASGI apps, it might not work the same way. Let me check if asgi_app supports the gpu parameter.Actually, looking at the Modal docs, `asgi_app` is decorated on a function that returns an ASGI app. The function itself runs on Modal's infrastructure. But I'm not sure if the `gpu` parameter on `@app.function()` passes through to the ASGI container.\n\nLet me try and see what happens. If it doesn't work, I'll need a different architecture.\n\nActually, maybe a better approach is: the ASGI app just does routing and doesn't need GPU. The actual inference is done by a separate GPU-enabled function that the ASGI app calls. \n\nSo I'd remove the GPU from the ASGI app itself and create a separate GPU-enabled function that handles all the heavy inference work. The tricky part is that each container gets its own GPU, so I need to make sure Ollama starts on the same container where the GPU is actually available.\n\nActually, let me just try putting the GPU parameter directly on the ASGI app function and see if Modal handles the routing automatically. If that doesn't work, I'll fall back to the separate function approach.","thinkingSignature":"2628e418b609e2efd52f2fafd1edf1ab57d24f78a1f17992db9a7ffca91ac487"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kms60bus9j48_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark; $env:PYTHONIOENCODING=\"utf-8\"; modal deploy modal_spark.py 2>&1","timeout":600}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":117632,"output":337,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131961,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":17