{"type":"message","id":"a839b487","parentId":"a2b23ffd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:30:33.824Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The HTML page still loads. But the `/health` endpoint is hanging and then timing out. This suggests the FastAPI route handler itself is blocking when trying to start Ollama.\n\nThe problem is in `health()` - when we call `loop.run_in_executor(None, _start_ollama_bg)`, it starts Ollama in a background thread. But then the `_ollama_state[\"status\"]` check happens and it's still \"unknown\" or \"starting\", so we return the status. But the issue is `loop.run_in_executor` might be blocking.\n\nActually, I think the problem is that the `/health` route itself is blocking when Ollama is starting. The `loop.run_in_executor` call happens but then the `health()` function returns immediately... unless the `loop.run_in_executor` itself is somehow blocking the event loop in an async context.\n \nI think I see it now - calling `run_in_executor` from within an async function actually blocks the event loop until the executor task completes, because the current thread can't handle other requests while waiting for the background task to finish. That's why the endpoint is hanging - the whole async handler is getting stuck waiting for Ollama to start, which prevents the response from being sent.\n\nThe real problem is that if Ollama takes 60 seconds to start, the health check will just timeout instead of returning a response. I need to make this truly non-blocking by using `asyncio.create_task()` instead, which schedules the coroutine to run without blocking the event loop.","thinkingSignature":"55002e79a8e68121fd218ea5958e15b2123d59b0fe1649b3b530e6deca44c194"},{"type":"text","text":"The health endpoint is blocking because `run_in_executor` still blocks the async event loop. Need to make it truly fire-and-forget:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yuhnyfdh4zva_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","oldText":"    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        # Trigger background start if not started\n        if _ollama_state[\"status\"] == \"unknown\":\n            # Fire and forget — start in background thread\n            loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()\n            loop.run_in_executor(None, _start_ollama_bg)\n\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"ollama\": _ollama_state[\"status\"],\n            \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n        }","newText":"    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        # Trigger background start if not started — truly non-blocking\n        if _ollama_state[\"status\"] == \"unknown\":\n            import concurrent.futures\n            executor = concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=1)\n            executor.submit(_start_ollama_bg)\n            # Don't wait — return immediately\n\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"ollama\": _ollama_state[\"status\"],\n            \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n        }"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":116538,"output":614,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131144,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326617413}}
{"type":"message","id":"5be3b953","parentId":"a839b487","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:30:33.878Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_yuhnyfdh4zva_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 224         return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n 225 \n 226     @api.get(\"/health\")\n 227     async def health():\n-228         # Trigger background start if not started\n+228         # Trigger background start if not started — truly non-blocking\n 229         if _ollama_state[\"status\"] == \"unknown\":\n-230             # Fire and forget — start in background thread\n-231             loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()\n-232             loop.run_in_executor(None, _start_ollama_bg)\n+230             import concurrent.futures\n+231             executor = concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=1)\n+232             executor.submit(_start_ollama_bg)\n+233             # Don't wait — return immediately\n 233 \n 234         return {\n 235             \"status\": \"ok\",\n 236             \"ollama\": _ollama_state[\"status\"],\n     ...","firstChangedLine":228},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326633853}}
