{"type":"message","id":"9122b9f6","parentId":"eecad78f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:31:31.855Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It connects to the server but hangs on the response. The server is receiving the request but not sending a response. This means the `/health` route is blocking somewhere.\n\nThe issue: `concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor()` creates a new executor and submits work. The executor might be blocking in a way that prevents the response from being sent.\n\nWait, actually - the issue might be that the Modal container is timing out during the cold start. The container is doing too much work at startup (starting Ollama in the background, pulling the model) and the request times out before the server even starts listening.\n\nActually no, the HTML page loads fine. The issue is specifically with the `/health` endpoint.\n \nSo the HTML loads because that endpoint doesn't call `_start_ollama_bg`, but the health endpoint does - and that function is making a blocking subprocess call to start Ollama and waiting for it to initialize. That's the bottleneck preventing the response from being sent.\n\nThe real issue is that `ThreadPoolExecutor.submit()` might not be truly async in FastAPI's context, or the server can't send a response while the background task is still blocking. I think the better approach is to defer the entire Ollama startup to a background task using FastAPI's `BackgroundTasks`, so the initial response can return immediately while the initialization happens asynchronously.","thinkingSignature":"0cf0f79f0e10fca34acdd5a4dfdc4f2cfbc733f1a071d554d0116b7d29d1f046"},{"type":"text","text":"The route is blocking because Ollama startup is synchronous. Let me use FastAPI's `BackgroundTasks` for proper async startup:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_grwv9e9jy92b_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","oldText":"@app.function(image=_image, timeout=3600, scaledown_window=600, gpu=\"A100\")\n@modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama\")\ndef api():\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n    import httpx\n\n    api = FastAPI()\n\n    @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\n    async def root():\n        return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        # Trigger background start if not started — truly non-blocking\n        if _ollama_state[\"status\"] == \"unknown\":\n            import concurrent.futures\n            executor = concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=1)\n            executor.submit(_start_ollama_bg)\n            # Don't wait — return immediately\n\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"ollama\": _ollama_state[\"status\"],\n            \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n        }","newText":"@app.function(image=_image, timeout=3600, scaledown_window=600, gpu=\"A100\")\n@modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama\")\ndef api():\n    from fastapi import FastAPI, BackgroundTasks\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n    import httpx\n\n    api = FastAPI()\n\n    @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\n    async def root():\n        return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health(background_tasks: BackgroundTasks):\n        if _ollama_state[\"status\"] == \"unknown\":\n            background_tasks.add_task(_start_ollama_bg)\n\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"ollama\": _ollama_state[\"status\"],\n            \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n        }"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":117596,"output":743,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132331,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326672296}}
{"type":"message","id":"a8c56500","parentId":"9122b9f6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:31:31.913Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_grwv9e9jy92b_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 212 \n 213 @app.function(image=_image, timeout=3600, scaledown_window=600, gpu=\"A100\")\n 214 @modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama\")\n 215 def api():\n-216     from fastapi import FastAPI\n+216     from fastapi import FastAPI, BackgroundTasks\n 217     from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n 218     import httpx\n 219 \n 220     api = FastAPI()\n 221 \n 222     @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\n 223     async def root():\n 224         return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n 225 \n 226     @api.get(\"/health\")\n-227     async def health():\n-228         # Trigger background start if not started — truly non-blocking\n+227     async def health(background_tasks: BackgroundTasks):\n 229         if _ollama_state[\"status\"] == \"unknown\":\n-230             import concurrent.futures\n-231             executor = concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=1)\n-232             executor.submit(_start_ollama_bg)\n-233             # Don't wait — return immediately\n+229             background_tasks.add_task(_start_ollama_bg)\n 234 \n 235         return {\n 236             \"status\": \"ok\",\n 237             \"ollama\": _ollama_state[\"status\"],\n     ...","firstChangedLine":216},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326691882}}
{"type":"message","id":"f8c752c0","parentId":"a8c56500","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:31:45.639Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but `BackgroundTasks` in FastAPI adds a task to run after the response is sent. But the tasks run in the same async event loop, and `_start_ollama_bg` is a blocking function (it calls `subprocess.Popen`, `time.sleep`, etc.). This will still block the event loop.\n\nActually, `BackgroundTasks` in FastAPI does run the task in a thread pool, so it should be fine. Let me check...\n\nFrom FastAPI docs: \"The background tasks are executed in a separate thread pool managed by FastAPI/Starlette, so they don't block the main async event loop.\" So yes, they run in a thread pool. This should work.","thinkingSignature":"ec7036ba197cc4bbc54ece19273cb5573b951657e80b7a7d6875ada3807f4329"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fd0kmidabb6q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark; $env:PYTHONIOENCODING=\"utf-8\"; modal deploy modal_spark.py 2>&1","timeout":600}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":117787,"output":216,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131995,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326691917}}
