{"type":"message","id":"c8d739cb","parentId":"624a9f34","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:32:43.052Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the server IS responding with 404 for unknown routes, which means the server is up. The issue is specifically with the `/health` endpoint.\n\nLet me think... the health endpoint is defined with `@api.get(\"/health\")`. It has `BackgroundTasks` as a parameter. Wait - could it be that Modal's ASGI app doesn't support `BackgroundTasks` dependency injection?\n\nActually, I just realized: Modal's ASGI wrapper might not support FastAPI's `BackgroundTasks` because they're handled by the ASGI app itself, not by Modal's infrastructure.\n\nLet me try a different approach - just check if we can return a simple response without the background task.","thinkingSignature":"435132ae59fdd0d0ff7296796d52a18628b00f8b1f77bd7cd1b180bb6c090212"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uh4xdvaj9wi2_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","oldText":"    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health(background_tasks: BackgroundTasks):\n        if _ollama_state[\"status\"] == \"unknown\":\n            background_tasks.add_task(_start_ollama_bg)\n\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"ollama\": _ollama_state[\"status\"],\n            \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n        }","newText":"    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        if _ollama_state[\"status\"] == \"unknown\":\n            import threading\n            t = threading.Thread(target=_start_ollama_bg, daemon=True)\n            t.start()\n\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"ollama\": _ollama_state[\"status\"],\n            \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n        }"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":114346,"output":352,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128690,"cost":{"input":0,