{"type":"message","id":"659f62d9","parentId":"b26bfece","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:34:01.605Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the server IS up and responding to requests. The root HTML loads and unknown routes return 404. But `/health` hangs and times out. This is very strange.\n\nThe only difference between `/` and `/health` is that `/health` calls `_start_ollama_bg()` in a daemon thread if `_ollama_state[\"status\"]` is \"unknown\". \n\nLet me think... `_ollama_state` is defined at module level. When the app starts, `_ollama_state[\"status\"]` is \"unknown\". On the first call to `/health`, we spawn a daemon thread that calls `_start_ollama_bg`. \n\nBut here's the problem: that daemon thread runs `subprocess.Popen` to start Ollama, which should detach and return immediately, then `_start_ollama_bg` waits for Ollama to be ready with a 2-second poll interval for up to 60 seconds. The thread is daemon so it shouldn't block the server shutdown, but maybe it's holding onto some resource that's preventing the response from being sent.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the real issue might be that the old container without the GPU is still running, and when I deploy with `gpu=\"A100\"`, Modal creates a new container with that requirement. The first request could be hitting either the old container (which lacks GPU support) or the new one (still initializing). The root HTML might work on both, but something about the `/health` endpoint is failing specifically.\n\nThe `scaledown_window=600` setting means the container stays alive for 10 minutes of inactivity, so it shouldn't be scaling down between my requests. Let me test with a longer timeout or just hit the `/` endpoint consistently and see if it starts failing too.","thinkingSignature":"6b2ccd744248c172e2eb51c70697dca6acb245d9e223ea2568b71f8bfd51bc6d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uruh50kgonny_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"for i in {1..5}; do echo \"Attempt $