{"type":"message","id":"8a1cb344","parentId":"87e6df97","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:50:13.412Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, `@modal.build()` isn't the right decorator for a one-time model pull. In Modal Cls classes, the `@modal.build()` decorator is for functions that run during the image build step. But I want the model to be pulled when the container starts (persistently), not at image build time.\n\nActually, for the `pull_model` to work, I should use it as a `@modal.method()` that gets called once when the container is first started, and then the state persists. But there's a problem: `pull_model` is a method on the class, and the `@modal.build()` decorator marks it as a build step.\n\n\nSo `@modal.build()` should work since it runs during the container build phase when the GPU is available, but the Ollama serve command needs to run persistently in the background after that setup completes. I also need to set `gpu=\"A100\"` on the `@modal.cls()` decorator itself rather than on individual methods.\n\nActually, I'm realizing that when `OllamaService` has `gpu=\"A100\"` at the class level, all its methods get GPU access, so I can keep the GPU setting centralized there. But I still need a way to run `ollama serve` as a persistent background process—either through a `@modal.background_task` or by running it directly in the class constructor or a `@modal.build()` method.\n\nThe real issue I'm running into is whether `@modal.build()` actually gives me GPU access during the build step, since that's when I'd want to pull the model. If not, I might need to use a dedicated GPU function to handle the model pull, or just run the pull command directly in the build step and accept that the first request might need to wait for it to complete.\n\nLet me think through the execution flow: when I deploy with `modal deploy`, the class builds with GPU access, `pull_model` runs to download the model, then the container starts and `_ensure_ollama()` launches the Ollama server as a background process before any requests hit the endpoint. The key is that `subprocess.Popen` starts the server without blocking, so the container can continue initializing while Ollama starts up in the background.\n\nI should remove the `@modal.build()` decorator entirely since the build step doesn't actually give me GPU access for pulling models, and instead rely on lazy initialization when the first request arrives. I'll also strip out the `gpu=` parameter from individual methods since it's already set at the class level.","thinkingSignature":"924b1654c8898146ba07c181e55d2aa89a82dd22a03fdb84732350c6fad05c3c"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me clean up the Cls approach — remove `@modal.build()` (doesn't give GPU), handle model pull lazily:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9yb8iya2wr49_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","oldText":"@app.cls(image=_image, gpu=\"A100\", timeout=3600, scaledown_window=600)\nclass OllamaService:\n    \"\"\"Stateful Ollama service — stays warm in a persistent container.\"\"\"\n\n    @modal.build()\n    def pull_model(self):\n        \"\"\"One-time model pull at build/deploy time.\"\"\"\n        print(f\"Pulling {MODEL_NAME}...\")\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\n            stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n        )\n        if result.returncode != 0:\n            print(\"Pull output:\", result.stdout.decode(errors=\"replace\"))\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Model pull failed: {result.returncode}\")\n        print(\"Model ready.\")\n\n    @modal.method()\n    def health(self):","newText":"@app.cls(image=_image, gpu=\"A100\", timeout=3600, scaledown_window=600)\nclass OllamaService:\n    \"\"\"Stateful Ollama service — stays warm in a persistent container.\"\"\"\n\n    @modal.method()\n    def health(self):"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":120016,"output":814,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134822,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774327788043}}
{"type":"message","id":"c91b7ab8","parentId":"8a1cb344","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:50:13.503Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9yb8iya2wr49_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  54 @app.cls(image=_image, gpu=\"A100\", timeout=3600, scaledown_window=600)\n  55 class OllamaService:\n  56     \"\"\"Stateful Ollama service — stays warm in a persistent container.\"\"\"\n  57 \n- 58     @modal.build()\n- 59     def pull_model(self):\n- 60         \"\"\"One-time model pull at build/deploy time.\"\"\"\n- 61         print(f\"Pulling {MODEL_NAME}...\")\n- 62         result = subprocess.run(\n- 63             [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\n- 64             stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n- 65         )\n- 66         if result.returncode != 0:\n- 67             print(\"Pull output:\", result.stdout.decode(errors=\"replace\"))\n- 68             raise RuntimeError(f\"Model pull failed: {result.returncode}\")\n- 69         print(\"Model ready.\")\n- 70 \n  71     @modal.method()\n  72     def health(self):\n  73         import httpx\n  74         try:\n     ...","firstChangedLine":58},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774327813460}}
{"type":"message","id":"4bb384c8","parentId":"c91b7ab8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:50:33.983Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the `_ensure_ollama` method to also pull the model if not present. And the `health` method needs to first check if Ollama is running and start it.","thinkingSignature":"4f86dd96a06b2a3ba4cdb7bffae40c18b38d3ac6cfb2b8a173b686632805d336"},{"type":"text","text":"Now update `_ensure_ollama` to pull model if missing:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rwx7bqelranp_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","oldText":"    def _ensure_ollama(self):\n        \"\"\"Start Ollama if not already running.\"\"\"\n        import httpx\n        try:\n            with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\n                r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                if r.status_code == 200:\n                    return\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n\n        # Try to start Ollama\n        subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"serve\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", str(OLLAMA_PORT)],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL, stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n        )\n        # Wait up to 60s for Ollama to come up\n        for i in range(30):\n            try:\n                with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\n                    r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                    if r.status_code == 200:\n                        return\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n            time.sleep(2)\n        raise RuntimeError(\"Ollama failed to start\")","newText":"    def _ensure_ollama(self):\n        \"\"\"Start Ollama if not already running. Pull model if missing.\"\"\"\n        import httpx\n        import subprocess\n\n        try:\n            with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\n                r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                if r.status_code == 200:\n                    return\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n\n        # Start Ollama\n        subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"serve\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", str(OLLAMA_PORT)],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL, stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n        )\n        # Wait for Ollama to come up\n        for i in range(30):\n            try:\n                with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\n                    r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                    if r.status_code == 200:\n                        break\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n            time.sleep(2)\n        else:\n            raise RuntimeError(\"Ollama API failed to start\")\n\n        # Check model\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"list\"],\n            capture_output=True, text=True,\n        )\n        if MODEL_NAME not in result.stdout:\n            print(f\"Pulling {MODEL_NAME} (first time, may take a few minutes)...\")\n            pull = subprocess.Popen(\n                [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\n                stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            )\n            for line in pull.stdout:\n                print(line.decode(errors=\"replace\"), end=\"\", flush=True)\n            pull.wait()\n            if pull.returncode != 0:\n                raise RuntimeError(f\"Model pull failed for {MODEL_NAME}\")\n            print(\"Model ready.\")"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":119048,"output":763,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133803,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774327813508}}
