{"type":"message","id":"e85d8b88","parentId":"3abf2217","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:51:21.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The app is still `spark-ollama` but there are two stopped `test-ollama` apps. The web function URL was empty - let me check if the web function was deployed. Let me check the web function URL more specifically.\n\nActually, looking at the deploy output again:\n```\n├── 🔨 Created function OllamaService.*.\n└── 🔨 Created web function web => \n    https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-web.modal.run\n```\n\nIt says `spark-ollama-web` - that's a different app name! The web function was created as `spark-ollama-web`. But the web URL shown is blank. Let me check the new app name.Actually, the deploy said `spark-ollama` still. \n\nI think the issue is that Modal deploys an ASGI app from a `@app.function` decorated with `@modal.asgi_app`, but the URL only appears after a successful deploy. Since I have both `OllamaService` as a class and `web` as a function with `@modal.asgi_app`, they might be conflicting with each other. The `spark-ollama-web` URL could just be an internal name. Let me test calling the health endpoint to see what happens.\n\nI need to find the actual URL for the new deploy. Looking at the output, I see `spark-ollama-web.modal.run` but that URL isn't resolving. I'm wondering if the web function is part of the `spark-ollama` app but the URL wasn't printed in the output. Let me check the old URL to see if it's still working.","thinkingSignature":"bf521bc1c0373d33bcda894baf10686d9a6d3f50d4d3b395b75ed2026ff880a5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7omsii7ft3g4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s --max-time 10 https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama.modal.run/ 2>&1 | head -1 && echo \"old URL works\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":119013,"output":400,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133405,"cost":{"