{"type":"message","id":"c50da17b","parentId":"ee2955a4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:53:10.270Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I need to think about this more carefully. `OllamaService()` creates a NEW instance every time. This means:\n1. Each request creates a new OllamaService instance\n2. Each instance might run in a different container (unless Modal routes to the same warm container)\n3. The `_ensure_ollama` startup logic runs every time\n\nThis is NOT what we want. We want the Ollama service to be persistent in ONE container.\n\nThe issue is: when calling `OllamaService().health.remote()`, Modal creates a new container for each call unless we use `.get()` to get the same instance.\n\nBut the error said \"Did you forget to instantiate the class first?\" which suggests `OllamaService.method.remote()` is wrong and `OllamaService().method.remote()` is right.\n \nI'm realizing the distinction here — `OllamaService()` gives me a local Python instance that Modal automatically converts to a stub for RPC calls, so the distinction between instance and class method might not matter as much as I thought. Let me just try the direct approach and see if it works.","thinkingSignature":"b063d2cc8522ad5e26e7c766c77fc6e563e4104f64cb07eea2485b3acea4d42c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a8d6frvaq5dv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark; $env:PYTHONIOENCODING=\"utf-8\"; modal deploy modal_spark.py 2>&1","timeout":600}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":100822,"output":301,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115115,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774327981510}}
