{"type":"message","id":"4f0b82ae","parentId":"924cb57e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:53:25.165Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is weird. The error says \"Did you forget to instantiate the class first?\" and suggests `MyClass().method.remote()`. But I changed it to `OllamaService().health.remote()`. Let me check if my edit was actually applied.Actually wait - the deployed code is from the mount `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py`. But when I deploy with `modal deploy`, it uses the mount. So the deployed code should be the updated one. Unless there's a caching issue.\n\nLet me re-read the current file to make sure the edit was applied:","thinkingSignature":"44d605a0c12fb96cd2bf283e10c4559f5c21dc5acc35ea9a3890f2b2cb423d0d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xlfokqzhs7dj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"OllamaService\" C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py | tail -10","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":101367,"output":193,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115552,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774327998500}}
