{"type":"message","id":"9544eeef","parentId":"fbd6b216","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:53:45.835Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The code is correct: `OllamaService().health.remote()`. But the error persists. This is very strange.\n\nWait - the error says \"Did you forget to instantiate the class first?\" with the exact phrasing I saw in the error. But I already changed the code to use `OllamaService()`.\n\nCould it be that the OLD code is cached somewhere? When `modal deploy` runs, it should upload the new file...\n\nActually, let me check: maybe the issue is that `OllamaService` is defined in the SAME file as the web function, but `OllamaService` is a `@modal.cls` decorated class. When the web function imports `OllamaService`, it's getting the class, not an instance.\n \nSo the real problem is that calling `OllamaService().health.remote()` creates a new instance on each request, which defeats the purpose of keeping Ollama running persistently. I need to look at the Modal documentation more carefully to understand the right pattern for accessing GPU classes from web functions.\n\nLooking at Modal's examples, the typical approach is to call the method directly on the class like `OllamaService.health.remote()`, but that's giving me an error. Let me reconsider whether I should just use the REST API pattern instead of trying to call the class methods directly from the web endpoint. Actually, I should step back and think about the architecture more broadly. Rather than trying to route through `OllamaService`, maybe I should use a `WebEndpoint` instead, which would let me call the Ollama API directly from the web function without needing to reference the class at all. Let me try switching to that approach and see if it simplifies things.","thinkingSignature":"289f6116558409e4a2675cc2da542197d34bb6ad5b5c135fe3c6695a0412bd29"},{"type":"text","text":"The class is importing but the instance call isn't working as expected. Let me switch to using `modal.web_endpoint` which can call Ollama directly without needing the class:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c5lnc3mmugmj_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","oldText":"@app.function(image=_web_image)\n@modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama-web\")\ndef web():\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n    api = FastAPI()\n\n    @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\n    async def root():\n        return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        try:\n            result = OllamaService().health.remote()\n            return result\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)}\n\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\n    async def generate(req: dict):\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\n        try:\n            result = OllamaService().generate.remote(\n                prompt=prompt, temperature=temperature, num_predict=num_predict\n            )\n            return result\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"error\": str(e)}\n\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\n    async def benchmarks():\n        try:\n            result = OllamaService().benchmarks.remote()\n            return result\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"error\": str(e)}\n\n    return api","newText":"@app.function(image=_web_image)\n@modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama-web\")\ndef web():\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n    import httpx\n    api = FastAPI()\n\n    @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\n    async def root():\n        return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        try:\n            # Check if OllamaService is ready by calling its health method\n            result = OllamaService().health.remote()\n            return result\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)}\n\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\n    async def generate(req: dict):\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\n        try:\n            result = OllamaService().generate.remote(\n                prompt=prompt, temperature=temperature, num_predict=num_predict\n            )\n            return result\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"error\": str(e)}\n\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\n    async def benchmarks():\n        try:\n            result = OllamaService().benchmarks.remote()\n            return result\n        except Exception as e:\n            return {\"error\": str(e)}\n\n    return api"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":101635,"output":1011,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116638,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774328005826}}
{"type":"message","id":"0432a284","parentId":"9544eeef","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:53:45.909Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_c5lnc3mmugmj_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 288 @modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama-web\")\n 289 def web():\n 290     from fastapi import FastAPI\n 291     from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n+292     import httpx\n 292     api = FastAPI()\n 293 \n 294     @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\n 295     async def root():\n 296         return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n 297 \n 298     @api.get(\"/health\")\n 299     async def health():\n 300         try:\n+302             # Check if OllamaService is ready by calling its health method\n 301             result = OllamaService().health.remote()\n 302             return result\n 303         except Exception as e:\n 304             return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)}\n     ...","firstChangedLine":292},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774328025877}}
{"type":"message","id":"4314f315","parentId":"0432a284","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:54:05.747Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I didn't actually change the logic - I just added the import. The problem is still `OllamaService().health.remote()` not working.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The issue is: `OllamaService` is a `@modal.cls` decorated class. When I call `OllamaService().health.remote()`, the `()` creates a local Python instance, but calling `.health.remote()` on it might not work because `health` is decorated with `@modal.method()`.\n\nActually, I wonder if the issue is that I need to call the method on the CLASS, not on an instance. Like: `OllamaService.health.remote()`. But that gives the same error.\n \nThe error message is pretty explicit though - \"Did you forget to instantiate the class first?\" means I do need the `()`. But maybe the problem is that `OllamaService` isn't being recognized as a Modal class at all. When the web function imports it from the same module where it's decorated, it should get the right stub, but maybe something's going wrong there.\n\nI think the real issue is that Modal web functions run in their own container without GPU access, so they're separate from the GPU container where `OllamaService` actually runs. The web container imports `OllamaService`, but since it's not a GPU container itself, there might be some mismatch in how Modal handles the `@modal.cls` decorator in that context.\n\nActually, the simpler explanation is probably that `OllamaService.health.remote()` requires an active Modal client to be initialized, which might not be available in the web container. I could try using `modal.forward` to create a tunnel directly to the `OllamaService` container, but that adds complexity. The most straightforward approach would be to use a `modal.WebEndpoint` for the web server and have it make direct HTTP calls to the Ollama service running in the GPU container on the internal port.\n\nBut wait—`WebEndpoint` functions don't run indefinitely; they only execute when a request comes in and then shut down. That means Ollama would need to be started for each request, which defeats the purpose of keeping it running persistently. I need to step back and rethink the architecture here.\n\nThe real solution is that `OllamaService` itself needs to be the persistent, always-on service that starts Ollama when the container initializes, then exposes an HTTP interface that the web function can call. Looking at Modal's patterns, when you have a `@modal.cls` class, you typically use `.get()` to obtain a specific named instance, or use `.from_name()` to retrieve an existing one—so the class acts as the gateway to the persistent service.\n\nThe pattern would be to instantiate the service once with `OllamaService()`, which creates a container with GPU access, and then call methods on that instance. But there's a subtlety here: calling `OllamaService().health.remote()` creates a new instance each time, which would spawn a fresh container. Instead, I should either use a static instance or leverage Modal's instance persistence to ensure all requests hit the same running container.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the `.health.remote()` call itself is what's failing with that instantiation error. The Modal SDK is rejecting the way I'm invoking the method on the class rather than through the proper remote call mechanism.\n\nLet me reconsider: maybe I need to use `.get()` to obtain a specific instance first, then call the method on that. Or perhaps I should just deploy and test this directly to see what Modal actually expects in this context.","thinkingSignature":"93add586f5a1858f3c8545b74b7385c6953f35c20e4486f96a9239cc56642856"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hio2grobdt1f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark; $env:PYTHONIOENCODING=\"utf-8\"; modal deploy modal_spark.py 2>&1","timeout":600}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":102684,"output":802,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117478,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774328025913}}
{"type":"message","id":"80ca9141","parentId":"4314f315","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:54:11.019Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hio2grobdt1f_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✓ Created objects.\r\n├── 🔨 Created mount C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py\r\n├── 🔨 Created function OllamaService.*.\r\n└── 🔨 Created web function web => \r\n    https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-web.modal.run\r\n✓ App deployed in 1.535s! 🎉\r\n\r\nView Deployment: https://modal.com/apps/toxzak-svg/main/deployed/spark-ollama"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5102,"aggregated":"✓ Created objects.\r\n├── 🔨 Created mount C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py\r\n├── 🔨 Created function OllamaService.*.\r\n└── 🔨 Created web function web => \r\n    https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-web.modal.run\r\n✓ App deployed in 1.535s! 🎉\r\n\r\nView Deployment: https://modal.com/apps/toxzak-svg/main/deployed/spark-ollama","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774328050931}}
{"type":"message","id":"37a1bae3","parentId":"80ca9141","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:55:09.848Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at how Modal Cls is supposed to work from a web context. Maybe the issue is that the web function needs to reference the class differently. Let me look at the actual Modal SDK source code for `_Cls`:\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach. Instead of calling `OllamaService` from the web function, let me just use a `modal.WebEndpoint` for the web UI and have it call Ollama directly. But then Ollama needs to be running somewhere persistent.\n\nOR - what if I just start Ollama in the same container as the web function? Give the web function `gpu=\"A100\"` too. Then Ollama starts when the web container starts, and everything is in one place.\n \nThe problem is that giving the web function a GPU would make it more expensive since it runs constantly, whereas OllamaService only runs when handling requests. But maybe that's worth it for simplicity - let me try combining them into a single class with the web endpoint.\n\nActually, I'm overcomplicating this. The cleanest approach is to put everything in one `@modal.asgi_app` with GPU allocation and start Ollama during the FastAPI startup event, then route all the inference calls through that same process.","thinkingSignature":"1ce20401a2bb3b381f97a840a982a3bf1f7b1357d72640325dda335c4a98d454"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me step back and use the simplest possible pattern — one GPU container that runs both Ollama and the web server together, starting Ollama in the background at startup:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ooq5jpmz7lli_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py","content":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama — single GPU container with FastAPI + Ollama + Eval Harness.\nOllama starts in background thread, stays warm while container is warm.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport time\nimport statistics\nimport threading\nimport os\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\nOLLAMA_PORT = 11434\nMODEL_NAME = \"qwen2.5:7b\"\n\n# ─── Benchmark prompts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nGSM8K = [\n    \"There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the orchard today. When they finished, there were 21 trees in the orchard. How many trees did they plant today?\",\n    \"Leah has 6 apples and 4 oranges, and she eats 2 fruits. How many fruits does she have left?\",\n    \"A clown has 12 balloons. He gives away 5 to children. Later he buys 8 more balloons. How many balloons does he have now?\",\n    \"Tom has 5 baseball cards. He buys 3 more packs with 4 cards each. How many cards does he have total?\",\n    \"There are 3 pink flowers and 4 blue flowers in a vase. Sarah puts 2 more pink flowers in the vase. How many flowers are in the vase?\",\n]\n\nREASONING = [\n    \"If all Zeps are Mors, and some Mors are Leps, could some Zeps be Leps? Explain your reasoning.\",\n    \"Complete the pattern: 2, 6, 12, 20, 30, ?\",\n    \"What is heavier: a pound of feathers or a pound of bricks?\",\n    \"If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 widgets?\",\n    \"A farmer has 17 sheep. All but 9 die. How many are left?\",\n]\n\nCODE = [\n    \"Write a Python function to check if a string is a palindrome.\",\n    \"Write a Python function that returns the nth Fibonacci number using iteration.\",\n    \"Write a Python function to find the maximum element in a list without using max().\",\n]\n\n# ─── Image: Ollama + FastAPI ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn[standard]\", \"httpx>=0.28.0\")\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd\",\n        \"curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )\n)\n\n# ─── Ollama lifecycle ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n_ollama_started = threading.Event()\n_ollama_ready = {\"status\": \"unknown\"}  # unknown | starting | ready | error\n\n\ndef _start_ollama():\n    \"\"\"Start Ollama and pull model. Runs in background thread.\"\"\"\n    import httpx\n    import subprocess\n\n    _ollama_ready[\"status\"] = \"starting\"\n\n    # Start Ollama server\n    proc = subprocess.Popen(\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"serve\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", str(OLLAMA_PORT)],\n        stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL, stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n    )\n\n    # Wait for API to come up\n    for i in range(30):\n        try:\n            with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\n                r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                if r.status_code == 200:\n                    break\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n        time.sleep(2)\n    else:\n        _ollama_ready[\"status\"] = \"error\"\n        return\n\n    # Check / pull model\n    result = subprocess.run(\n        [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"list\"],\n        capture_output=True, text=True,\n    )\n    if MODEL_NAME not in result.stdout:\n        print(f\"Pulling {MODEL_NAME} (first time, ~5GB, may take a few minutes)...\")\n        pull = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\n            stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n        )\n        for line in pull.stdout:\n            print(line.decode(errors=\"replace\"), end=\"\", flush=True)\n        pull.wait()\n        if pull.returncode != 0:\n            _ollama_ready[\"status\"] = \"error\"\n            return\n\n    _ollama_ready[\"status\"] = \"ready\"\n    _ollama_started.set()\n    print(f\"Ollama ready on port {OLLAMA_PORT} with model {MODEL_NAME}\")\n\n\n# ─── Web server ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n@app.function(image=_image, gpu=\"A100\", timeout=3600, scaledown_window=600)\n@modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama\")\ndef api():\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n    import httpx\n\n    api = FastAPI()\n\n    # Fire off Ollama startup in background (container startup = one-time cost)\n    if not _ollama_started.is_set():\n        t = threading.Thread(target=_start_ollama, daemon=True)\n        t.start()\n\n    @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\n    async def root():\n        return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"ollama\": _ollama_ready[\"status\"],\n            \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n        }\n\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\n    async def generate(req: dict):\n        if _ollama_ready[\"status\"] != \"ready\":\n            return {\"error\": f\"Ollama not ready ({_ollama_ready['status']}). Try again shortly.\"}\n\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n            r = await c.post(\n                f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                      \"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": num_predict, \"stream\": False}\n            )\n            r.raise_for_status()\n            return r.json()\n\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\n    async def benchmarks():\n        if _ollama_ready[\"status\"] != \"ready\":\n            return {\"error\": f\"Ollama not ready ({_ollama_ready['status']}). Try again shortly.\"}\n\n        BENCHMARK_PROMPTS = {\"gsm8k\": GSM8K, \"reasoning\": REASONING, \"code\": CODE}\n        results = {\"benchmarks\": [], \"timestamp\": time.time()}\n\n        for bench_name, prompts in BENCHMARK_PROMPTS.items():\n            bench_results, latencies = [], []\n            for prompt in prompts:\n                t0 = time.perf_counter()\n                try:\n                    async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n                        r = await c.post(\n                            f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                            json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                                  \"temperature\": 0.7, \"num_predict\": 300, \"stream\": False}\n                        )\n                        r.raise_for_status()\n                        response_text = r.json().get(\"response\", \"\")\n                except Exception as e:\n                    response_text = f\"ERROR: {str(e)}\"\n                latency = time.perf_counter() - t0\n                latencies.append(latency)\n                bench_results.append({\n                    \"prompt\": prompt,\n                    \"response\": response_text,\n                    \"latency_s\": round(latency, 3),\n                })\n            results[\"benchmarks\"].append({\n                \"name\": bench_name,\n                \"num_prompts\": len(prompts),\n                \"avg_latency_s\": round(statistics.mean(latencies), 3),\n                \"total_time_s\": round(sum(latencies), 3),\n                \"results\": bench_results,\n            })\n        return results\n\n    return api\n\n\n# ─── UI HTML ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nUI_HTML = \"\"\"<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"/><title>SPARK Eval</title><style>\n*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;background:#0f0f13;color:#e0e0e0;min-height:100vh}\n#root{padding:2rem;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}h1{color:#fff;margin-bottom:1.5rem}\n.card{background:#1a1a22;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border:1px solid #2a2a35}\n.card h2{color:#a0a0b0;font-size:.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:1rem}\nbutton{background:#6366f1;color:white;border:none;padding:.6rem 1.2rem;border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer;font-size:.9rem;font-weight:500}\nbutton:hover{background:#4f46e5}button:disabled{background:#3a3a4a;cursor:not-allowed}\n.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:.75rem}\n.stat-card{background:#14141c;border-radius:8px;padding:.9rem;border:1px solid #252530}\n.stat-card h3{color:#fff;margin-bottom:.4rem;font-size:.95rem}\n.s{color:#707080;font-size:.82rem;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:.2rem 0}\n.s span{color:#c0c0d0;font-family:monospace}\n.res{margin-top:.8rem;padding-top:.8rem;border-top:1px solid #252530}\n.q{color:#888898;font-size:.82rem;margin-bottom:.4rem}\n.a{color:#d0d0e0;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.5;background:#101018;padding:.7rem;border-radius:6px;white-space:pre-wrap}\n.lat{color:#6366f1;font-size:.75rem;margin-top:.3rem}\n.expander{cursor:pointer;padding:.4rem 0}.expander:hover{color:#fff}\n.header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-bottom:2rem;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.8rem}\n.badge{background:#252530;padding:.35rem .75rem;border-radius:6px;font-size:.78rem;color:#a0a0b0}\ninput{background:#14141c;border:1px solid #252530;color:#e0e0e0;padding:.6rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:.9rem;flex:1}\n.gen-form{display:flex;gap:.5rem;margin-bottom:.8rem}\n.status{font-size:.8rem}.ok{color:#22c55e}.err{color:#ef4444}.warn{color:#f59e0b}\n</style></head><body><div id=\"root\"></div>\n<script type=\"module\">\nimport React,{useState,useEffect}from\"react\";import ReactDOM from\"react-dom/client\";import axios from\"axios\"\nconst API=\"\"\nconst App=()=>{\n  const[benchmarks,setBenchmarks]=useState(null)\n  const[loading,setLoading]=useState(false)\n  const[health,setHealth]=useState(null)\n  const[expanded,setExpanded]=useState({})\n  const[prompt,setPrompt]=useState(\"\")\n  const[genResult,setGenResult]=useState(null)\n  const[genning,setGening]=useState(false)\n  useEffect(()=>{(async()=>{try{const r=await axios.get(API+\"/health\");setHealth(r.data)}catch(e){setHealth({status:\"error\",error:e.message})}})()},[])\n  const run=async()=>{setLoading(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/benchmarks\");setBenchmarks(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setLoading(false)}\n  const send=async(e)=>{e.preventDefault();if(!prompt.trim())return;setGening(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/generate\",{prompt,temperature:.7,num_predict:300});setGenResult(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setGening(false)}\n  const toggle=(b,i)=>{const k=b+\"-\"+i;setExpanded(p=>({...p,[k]:!p[k]}))}\n  const healthColor=health?.ollama===\"ready\"?\"ok\":health?.ollama===\"starting\"?\"warn\":\"err\"\n  const healthText=health?.ollama===\"ready\"?\"Ollama Ready\":health?.ollama===\"starting\"?\"Starting...\":\"Offline\"\n  return React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"header\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h1\",null,\"SPARK Eval\"),\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{style:{display:\"flex\",gap:\"1rem\",alignItems:\"center\"}},\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"badge\"},\"qwen2.5:7b\"),\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"status \"+healthColor},healthText),\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{onClick:run,disabled:loading},loading?\"Running...\":\"Run Benchmarks\")\n      )\n    ),\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Chat\"),\n      React.createElement(\"form\",{className:\"gen-form\",onSubmit:send},\n        React.createElement(\"input\",{value:prompt,onChange:e=>setPrompt(e.target.value),placeholder:\"Ask the model...\"}),\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{type:\"submit\",disabled:genning},genning?\"...\":\"Send\")\n      ),\n      genResult&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},genResult.response)\n    ),\n    benchmarks&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Results\"),\n        React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"grid\"},\n          benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"stat-card\"},\n            React.createElement(\"h3\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Prompts\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.num_prompts)),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Avg Latency\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.avg_latency_s+\"s\")),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Total Time\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.total_time_s+\"s\"))\n          ))\n        )\n      ),\n      benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"card\"},\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()+\" Responses\"),\n        b.results.map((r,i)=>{\n          const k=b.name+\"-\"+i\n          return React.createElement(\"div\",{key:i,className:\"res\"},\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"expander\",onClick:()=>toggle(b.name,i)},\n              React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"q\"},\"Q: \"+r.prompt.slice(0,85)+(r.prompt.length>85?\"...\":\"\")),\n              React.createElement(\"span\",{style:{color:\"#6366f1\",fontSize:\".75rem\",marginLeft:\".5rem\"}},expanded[k]?\"▲\":\"▼\")\n            ),\n            expanded[k]&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n              React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},\"A: \"+r.response),\n              React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"lat\"},r.latency_s+\"s\")\n            )\n          )\n        })\n      ))\n    ),\n    !benchmarks&&!loading&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Ready\"),\n      React.createElement(\"p\",{style:{color:\"#707080\",fontSize:\".88rem\"}},'Click \"Run Benchmarks\" to evaluate the model.')\n    )\n  )\n}\nReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById(\"root\")).render(React.createElement(App))\n</script></body></html>\"\"\"\n\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef main():\n    print(\"Deploying SPARK — GPU container with Ollama + FastAPI\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":103600,"output":4033,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121625,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774328051044}}
