{"type":"message","id":"5cecbc11","parentId":"1d47f97e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:29:14.085Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach sent training logs from an SRMoE (Sparse Routing Mixture of Experts) training run, plus a PDF. Let me analyze the logs:\n\n**Phase 1: Supervised pre-training (2000 epochs)**\n\nLooking at the metrics:\n- `loss`: Started at 5.7507, went down to 2.3685 — good convergence\n- `acc`: Started at 0.000 (random init), peaked at 0.900 at ep 200, settled around 0.800 — this is weird though, acc dropped from 0.900 to 0.800 while loss also dropped, suggesting the model might be getting more confident but less accurate, or there's a distribution shift\n\n\n- `route_ce`: Routing cross-entropy staying flat around 1.06-1.15 means the router isn't learning to route meaningfully\n- `div`: Diversity metric hovering around 0.06 is extremely low, so it's barely using any experts\n- `wr` and `rd`: Both negligible at 0.11, indicating almost no weighted routing or regularization happening\n- `skip`: Stabilized at 0.79, which is problematic — the model is skipping 79% of forward passes, likely routing to a default or null expert instead of the actual MoE layers\n- `occ`: Around 17.3, though the units are unclear for this metric\n\nThe core problems seem to be that the router isn't actually learning to route between experts, the model isn't leveraging its mixture of experts architecture effectively, and there's an extremely high skip rate that's preventing proper MoE utilization.","thinkingSignature":"c98325062ca12962163a5bbd5abcfd9ca84f9ef8fa7bdb11b4e2324b7bef19c4"},{"type":"text","text":"The logs are interesting but the PDF didn't come through as text. Can you paste the key plots or key numbers from the PDF? A few things I noticed from the logs:\n\n**Red flags:**\n- `skip=0.79` — model is skipping ~79% of forward passes entirely. That's not a MoE, that's a router that mostly says \"skip everything\"\n- `route_ce` barely moved (1.15 → 1.05) — the router isn't learning to route meaningfully\n- `div=0.06` — essentially zero expert diversity, all traffic going to the same experts\n- `acc` peaked at 0.90 at ep 200 then dropped to 0.80 while loss kept falling — sounds like the model is converging to predicting one class\n\n**The skip rate is the biggest issue.** Typical MoE should have skip < 0.1. 0.79 means your auxiliary load balancing loss or whatever is enforcing \"route somewhere\" isn't working properly, or the routing decision is defaulting to a null/identity pass.\n\nWhat does the PDF show for expert utilization distribution? And what loss function are you using for the routing — is it a hard routingAuxiliary loss, or something else?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":584,"cacheRead":117087,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117671,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774330127905}}
