{"type":"message","id":"45395e05","parentId":"300d2fca","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:31:17.020Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_yy4aiigbi34x_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: nano-pdf\ndescription: Edit PDFs with natural-language instructions using the nano-pdf CLI.\nhomepage: https://pypi.org/project/nano-pdf/\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"emoji\": \"📄\",\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"nano-pdf\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"uv\",\n              \"kind\": \"uv\",\n              \"package\": \"nano-pdf\",\n              \"bins\": [\"nano-pdf\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install nano-pdf (uv)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# nano-pdf\n\nUse `nano-pdf` to apply edits to a specific page in a PDF using a natural-language instruction.\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nnano-pdf edit deck.pdf 1 \"Change the title to 'Q3 Results' and fix the typo in the subtitle\"\n```\n\nNotes:\n\n- Page numbers are 0-based or 1-based depending on the tool’s version/config; if the result looks off by one, retry with the other.\n- Always sanity-check the output PDF before sending it out.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774330276992}}
