{"type":"message","id":"b0f04957","parentId":"34e6b6e7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:52:23.972Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me make the fixes to the notebook. I need to:\n\n1. Remove `detach()` on hidden state for routing\n2. Mix query-phase oracle into Phase 1\n3. Soft transition into Phase 2 (gradual reduction of oracle routing)\n4. Minimum route density penalty\n\nLet me read the notebook again and make targeted edits.","thinkingSignature":"3201e97c2e40d532f3923a80b79cacddf076691fdff9fd7dc14548b1444f8801"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cpaje5zsnsk4_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb","offset":1,"limit":500}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":127,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":105175,"totalTokens":119337,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774331534570}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f9132e4","parentId":"b0f04957","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:52:24.073Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cpaje5zsnsk4_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n \"cells\": [\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n   \"id\": \"b7bb99b5\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"source\": [\n    \"# SR-MoE Training\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"**Sparse Routing Mixture-of-Experts** with popcode VQ codebook + ring attractor.\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"This notebook trains the SR-MoE routing architecture end-to-end on the associative\\n\",\n    \"memory task. Run all cells in sequence.\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"## What is SR-MoE?\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"1. **Popcode Router** — replaces softmax with a learned VQ codebook. The router\\n\",\n    \"   selects a discrete codeword (one of N codes), each of which is a distribution\\n\",\n    \"   over the 3 routing actions. Closer to cortical sparse coding than MoE gating.\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"2. **Ring Attractor** — a 2D continuous attractor maintains routing state across\\n\",\n    \"   steps. Routing decisions depend on both the current token and the ring phase,\\n\",\n    \"   making routing path-dependent (vs stateless per-token softmax).\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"3. **Adversarial Diversity Regularizer** — penalizes code collapse (usage imbalance\\n\",\n    \"   + low code separation) so all codes stay active.\\n\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n   \"execution_count\": null,\n   \"id\": \"0397ebd3\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"outputs\": [\n    {\n     \"name\": \"stderr\",\n     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n     \"text\": [\n      \"\\u001b[33mWARNING: Running pip as the 'root' user can result in broken permissions and conflicting behaviour with the system package manager. It is recommended to use a virtual environment instead: https://pip.pypa.io/warnings/venv\\u001b[0m\\u001b[33m\\n\",\n      \"\\u001b[0m\"\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n     \"text\": [\n      \"torch: 2.1.1+cu121\\n\",\n      \"GPU available: True\\n\",\n      \"GPU: Quadro RTX 5000\\n\"\n     ]\n    }\n   ],\n   \"source\": [\n    \"import subprocess, sys\\n\",\n    \"subprocess.run([sys.executable, '-m', 'pip', 'install', 'numpy', 'wandb', '--quiet'], check=True)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"import os, math, random, json, time\\n\",\n    \"import torch\\n\",\n    \"import torch.nn as nn\\n\",\n    \"import torch.nn.functional as F\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"print('torch:', torch.__version__)\\n\",\n    \"print('GPU available:', torch.cuda.is_available())\\n\",\n    \"if torch.cuda.is_available():\\n\",\n    \"    print('GPU:', torch.cuda.get_device_name(0))\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"DEVICE = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\\n\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n   \"execution_count\": null,\n   \"id\": \"e0481840\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"outputs\": [\n    {\n     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n     \"text\": [\n      \"SR-MoE components loaded OK\\n\"\n     ]\n    }\n   ],\n   \"source\": [\n    \"# Constants\\n\",\n    \"N_ACTIONS = 3   # SKIP=0, READ=1, WRITE=2\\n\",\n    \"ORACLE_TO_ACTION_IDX = {'SKIP': 0, 'READ': 1, 'WRITE': 2, 'PERCEIVE': 0}\\n\",\n    \"IGNORE_INDEX = -100\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"# Ring Attractor\\n\",\n    \"class RingAttractor(nn.Module):\\n\",\n    \"    def __init__(self, hidden_dim, ring_dim=16, n_prefs=32, dt=0.5, decay=0.95):\\n\",\n    \"        super().__init__()\\n\",\n    \"        self.hidden_dim = hidden_dim; self.ring_dim = ring_dim\\n\",\n    \"        self.n_prefs = n_prefs; self.dt = dt; self.decay = decay\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        self.register_buffer('_prefs',\\n\",\n    \"            torch.linspace(0, 2*math.pi, n_prefs, dtype=torch.float32))\\n\",\n    \"        self.input_proj = nn.Sequential(\\n\",\n    \"            nn.Linear(hidden_dim, ring_dim*2), nn.Tanh())\\n\",\n    \"        self.lateral_w = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(n_prefs, n_prefs))\\n\",\n    \"        self._init_lateral_weights()\\n\",\n    \"        self._ring_state = None\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def _init_lateral_weights(self):\\n\",\n    \"        with torch.no_grad():\\n\",\n    \"            d = self._prefs.unsqueeze(1) - self._prefs.unsqueeze(0)\\n\",\n    \"            d = torch.atan2(torch.sin(d), torch.cos(d))\\n\",\n    \"            exc = torch.exp(-0.5*(d/2.0)**2)\\n\",\n    \"            inh = 0.3*torch.exp(-0.5*(d/5.0)**2)\\n\",\n    \"            w = (exc - inh) / (exc - inh).abs().mean() * 0.1\\n\",\n    \"            self.lateral_w.copy_(w)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def reset(self): self._ring_state = None\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def forward(self, hidden):\\n\",\n    \"        is_1d = hidden.dim() == 1\\n\",\n    \"        if is_1d: hidden = hidden.unsqueeze(0)\\n\",\n    \"        batch_size = hidden.shape[0]\\n\",\n    \"        ri = self.input_proj(hidden)\\n\",\n    \"        theta = torch.atan2(ri[..., 1], ri[..., 0])\\n\",\n    \"        prev = self._ring_state\\n\",\n    \"        if prev is None:\\n\",\n    \"            prev = torch.zeros(self.n_prefs, device=hidden.device)\\n\",\n    \"        prev_2d = prev.unsqueeze(0)\\n\",\n    \"        drive = F.relu(torch.cos(self._prefs.unsqueeze(0) - theta.unsqueeze(1)))\\n\",\n    \"        lateral = (self.lateral_w @ prev).unsqueeze(0).expand(batch_size, -1)\\n\",\n    \"        new_state = prev_2d + self.dt * (drive + 0.3*lateral - prev_2d - self.decay*prev_2d)\\n\",\n    \"        new_state = F.relu(new_state)\\n\",\n    \"        new_state = new_state / (new_state.sum(dim=-1, keepdim=True) + 1e-8)\\n\",\n    \"        self._ring_state = new_state.squeeze(0).detach()\\n\",\n    \"        return self._ring_state\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def get_state(self):\\n\",\n    \"        return self._ring_state if self._ring_state is not None else \\\\\\n\",\n    \"               torch.zeros(self.n_prefs, device=next(self.parameters()).device)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"# Diversity Regularizer\\n\",\n    \"class DiversityRegularizer(nn.Module):\\n\",\n    \"    def __init__(self, n_codes, lambda_usage=0.05, lambda_discrim=0.025):\\n\",\n    \"        super().__init__()\\n\",\n    \"        self.n_codes = n_codes\\n\",\n    \"        self.lambda_usage = lambda_usage\\n\",\n    \"        self.lambda_discrim = lambda_discrim\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def forward(self, codebook, pre_code_logits, code_indices):\\n\",\n    \"        device = codebook.device\\n\",\n    \"        batch_size = code_indices.shape[0]\\n\",\n    \"        usage_hist = torch.zeros(self.n_codes, device=device)\\n\",\n    \"        for idx in code_indices: usage_hist[idx] += 1\\n\",\n    \"        usage_p = usage_hist / (batch_size + 1e-8)\\n\",\n    \"        usage_entropy = -(usage_p * (usage_p + 1e-8).log()).sum()\\n\",\n    \"        usage_loss = 1.0 - usage_entropy / (math.log(self.n_codes) + 1e-8)\\n\",\n    \"        cb_probs = F.softmax(codebook, dim=-1)\\n\",\n    \"        discrimin_loss = torch.tensor(0.0, device=device)\\n\",\n    \"        n_pairs = 0\\n\",\n    \"        for i in range(self.n_codes):\\n\",\n    \"            for j in range(i+1, self.n_codes):\\n\",\n    \"                kl = F.kl_div(cb_probs[i].log().unsqueeze(0),\\n\",\n    \"                              cb_probs[j].unsqueeze(0), reduction='batchmean')\\n\",\n    \"                discrimin_loss += F.relu(0.5 - kl)\\n\",\n    \"                n_pairs += 1\\n\",\n    \"        if n_pairs > 0: discrimin_loss /= n_pairs\\n\",\n    \"        loss = self.lambda_usage * usage_loss + self.lambda_discrim * discrimin_loss\\n\",\n    \"        return loss, {'usage': usage_loss.item(), 'discrim': discrimin_loss.item()}\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"# SR-MoE Head\\n\",\n    \"class SRMoEHead(nn.Module):\\n\",\n    \"    def __init__(self, hidden_dim, n_codes=16, ring_dim=16, n_prefs=32,\\n\",\n    \"                 tau_start=1.0, tau_end=0.01, anneal_steps=5000, lambda_div=0.1):\\n\",\n    \"        super().__init__()\\n\",\n    \"        self.hidden_dim = hidden_dim; self.n_codes = n_codes\\n\",\n    \"        self._tau_start = tau_start; self._tau_end = tau_end\\n\",\n    \"        self.anneal_steps = anneal_steps\\n\",\n    \"        self._step = 0; self._eval_mode = False\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        self.ring = RingAttractor(hidden_dim, ring_dim, n_prefs)\\n\",\n    \"        self.encoder = nn.Sequential(\\n\",\n    \"            nn.Linear(hidden_dim + 4 + ring_dim, hidden_dim), nn.Tanh(),\\n\",\n    \"            nn.Linear(hidden_dim, n_codes))\\n\",\n    \"        self.ring_state_proj = nn.Linear(n_prefs, ring_dim)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        cb = torch.zeros(n_codes, N_ACTIONS)\\n\",\n    \"        for i in range(n_codes): cb[i, i % N_ACTIONS] = 1.0\\n\",\n    \"        self.codebook = nn.Parameter(cb)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        self.div_reg = DiversityRegularizer(n_codes,\\n\",\n    \"            lambda_usage=lambda_div*0.5, lambda_discrim=lambda_div*0.25)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    @property\\n\",\n    \"    def tau(self):\\n\",\n    \"        if self._eval_mode: return 0.0\\n\",\n    \"        frac = min(self._step / max(self.anneal_steps, 1), 1.0)\\n\",\n    \"        return self._tau_start + frac * (self._tau_end - self._tau_start)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def set_eval_mode(self, hard=True): self._eval_mode = hard\\n\",\n    \"    def reset(self): self._step = 0; self.ring.reset()\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def forward(self, hidden, budget_remaining, step_pos, step_parity, is_query_phase):\\n\",\n    \"        self._step += 1\\n\",\n    \"        h = hidden.view(-1)\\n\",\n    \"        self.ring(h)\\n\",\n    \"        rs = self.ring.get_state()\\n\",\n    \"        rp = torch.tanh(self.ring_state_proj(rs))\\n\",\n    \"        extra = torch.tensor([budget_remaining, step_pos, step_parity, is_query_phase],\\n\",\n    \"                           dtype=torch.float, device=hidden.device)\\n\",\n    \"        x = torch.cat([h, extra, rp], dim=-1)\\n\",\n    \"        pre_code = self.encoder(x)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        if self._eval_mode or self.tau <= 0:\\n\",\n    \"            code_idx = pre_code.argmax().item()\\n\",\n    \"        else:\\n\",\n    \"            gumbel = F.gumbel_softmax(pre_code.unsqueeze(0), tau=self.tau, hard=True)\\n\",\n    \"            code_idx = int(gumbel.argmax().item())\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        sel = F.embedding(torch.tensor([code_idx], device=hidden.device), self.codebook).squeeze(0)\\n\",\n    \"        action_logits = sel + (self.codebook[code_idx] - self.codebook[code_idx]).detach()\\n\",\n    \"        action_idx = int(action_logits.argmax().item())\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        probs = F.softmax(action_logits, dim=-1)\\n\",\n    \"        entropy = -(probs * (probs + 1e-9).log()).sum().item()\\n\",\n    \"        salience_entropy = entropy / math.log(N_ACTIONS)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        return action_logits, action_idx, salience_entropy\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def diversity_loss(self, hidden, budget_remaining):\\n\",\n    \"        h = hidden.view(-1)\\n\",\n    \"        rs = self.ring.get_state()\\n\",\n    \"        rp = torch.tanh(self.ring_state_proj(rs))\\n\",\n    \"        extra = torch.tensor([budget_remaining, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0],\\n\",\n    \"                           dtype=torch.float, device=hidden.device)\\n\",\n    \"        x = torch.cat([h, extra, rp], dim=-1)\\n\",\n    \"        pre_code = self.encoder(x)\\n\",\n    \"        code_probs = F.softmax(pre_code, dim=-1)\\n\",\n    \"        code_idx = code_probs.argmax().item()\\n\",\n    \"        return self.div_reg(self.codebook, pre_code.unsqueeze(0),\\n\",\n    \"                          torch.tensor([code_idx], device=hidden.device))\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"print('SR-MoE components loaded OK')\\n\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n   \"execution_count\": null,\n   \"id\": \"d7656822\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"outputs\": [\n    {\n     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n     \"text\": [\n      \"ArchitectureB loaded OK\\n\"\n     ]\n    }\n   ],\n   \"source\": [\n    \"# Architecture B (simplified)\\n\",\n    \"V_KEY_VAL = 50; V_FILLER = 10; V_TOTAL = V_KEY_VAL + V_FILLER\\n\",\n    \"OUTPUT_VOCAB = V_KEY_VAL\\n\",\n    \"EPISODE_LENGTH = 190; QUERY_START = 150\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"class FrozenEmbedding(nn.Module):\\n\",\n    \"    def __init__(self, v_total=V_TOTAL, d_embed=64, seed=0):\\n\",\n    \"        super().__init__()\\n\",\n    \"        g = torch.Generator().manual_seed(seed)\\n\",\n    \"        self.register_buffer('weight', F.normalize(torch.randn(v_total, d_embed, generator=g), dim=-1))\\n\",\n    \"    def forward(self, token_ids): return F.embedding(token_ids, self.weight)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"class BudgetEnforcer:\\n\",\n    \"    def __init__(self, B=20, T_window=100):\\n\",\n    \"        self.B, self.T_window = B, T_window; self._reset()\\n\",\n    \"    def _reset(self):\\n\",\n    \"        self.accesses = []; self.total_permitted = 0\\n\",\n    \"        self.blocked = 0; self.requested = 0\\n\",\n    \"    def step(self, action_idx):\\n\",\n    \"        self.requested += 1\\n\",\n    \"        if action_idx == 0: return True\\n\",\n    \"        window = self.accesses[max(0, len(self.accesses)-self.T_window):]\\n\",\n    \"        if len(window) >= self.B: self.blocked += 1; return False\\n\",\n    \"        self.accesses.append(action_idx); self.total_permitted += 1; return True\\n\",\n    \"    @property\\n\",\n    \"    def budget_remaining(self):\\n\",\n    \"        window = self.accesses[max(0, len(self.accesses)-self.T_window):]\\n\",\n    \"        return max(0, self.B - len(window))\\n\",\n    \"    @property\\n\",\n    \"    def budget_remaining_normalised(self): return self.budget_remaining / self.B\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"class ExternalMemory(nn.Module):\\n\",\n    \"    def __init__(self, capacity=200, key_dim=64, value_dim=64, write_threshold=0.5):\\n\",\n    \"        super().__init__()\\n\",\n    \"        self.capacity = capacity; self.key_dim = key_dim\\n\",\n    \"        self.value_dim = value_dim; self.write_threshold = write_threshold\\n\",\n    \"        self.reset()\\n\",\n    \"    def reset(self): self.keys = []; self.values = []; self.saliences = []\\n\",\n    \"    def write(self, key, value, salience=1.0, override_threshold=False):\\n\",\n    \"        if salience < self.write_threshold and not override_threshold: return\\n\",\n    \"        if len(self.keys) >= self.capacity:\\n\",\n    \"            idx = self.saliences.index(min(self.saliences))\\n\",\n    \"            self.keys.pop(idx); self.values.pop(idx); self.saliences.pop(idx)\\n\",\n    \"        self.keys.append(key.detach()); self.values.append(value.detach())\\n\",\n    \"        self.saliences.append(salience)\\n\",\n    \"    def read(self, query):\\n\",\n    \"        if not self.keys:\\n\",\n    \"            return torch.zeros(self.value_dim, device=query.device), torch.tensor(0.0)\\n\",\n    \"        keys_t = torch.stack([k.squeeze(0) if k.dim()>1 else k for k in self.keys])\\n\",\n    \"        scores = F.cosine_similarity(query.unsqueeze(0), keys_t, dim=-1)\\n\",\n    \"        idx = scores.argmax().item()\\n\",\n    \"        return self.values[idx].to(query.device), scores[idx]\\n\",\n    \"    @property\\n\",\n    \"    def occupancy(self): return len(self.keys)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"class ArchitectureB(nn.Module):\\n\",\n    \"    def __init__(self, d_embed=64, hidden_dim=128, budget_B=55, budget_T=190,\\n\",\n    \"                 write_threshold=0.5, embed_seed=0, use_sr_moe=True,\\n\",\n    \"                 n_codes=16, ring_dim=16, n_prefs=32, lambda_div=0.1,\\n\",\n    \"                 tau_start=1.0, tau_end=0.01, anneal_steps=5000):\\n\",\n    \"        super().__init__()\\n\",\n    \"        self.d_embed = d_embed; self.hidden_dim = hidden_dim\\n\",\n    \"        self.budget_B = budget_B; self.budget_T = budget_T\\n\",\n    \"        self.write_threshold = write_threshold; self.use_sr_moe = use_sr_moe\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        self.embedding = FrozenEmbedding(V_TOTAL, d_embed, seed=embed_seed)\\n\",\n    \"        self.gru = nn.GRUCell(d_embed + d_embed, hidden_dim)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        if use_sr_moe:\\n\",\n    \"            self.routing = SRMoEHead(hidden_dim, n_codes=n_codes, ring_dim=ring_dim,\\n\",\n    \"                                     n_prefs=n_prefs, tau_start=tau_start, tau_end=tau_end,\\n\",\n    \"                                     anneal_steps=anneal_steps, lambda_div=lambda_div)\\n\",\n    \"        else:\\n\",\n    \"            self.routing = nn.Sequential(\\n\",\n    \"                nn.Linear(hidden_dim+4, hidden_dim), nn.ReLU(),\\n\",\n    \"                nn.Linear(hidden_dim, 3))\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        self.memory = ExternalMemory(200, d_embed, d_embed, write_threshold)\\n\",\n    \"        self.budget = BudgetEnforcer(budget_B, budget_T)\\n\",\n    \"        self.output_head = nn.Linear(hidden_dim + d_embed, OUTPUT_VOCAB)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        self._hidden = None; self._step = 0\\n\",\n    \"        self._pending_write_key = None; self._prev_emb = None\\n\",\n    \"        self._primed_oracle_actions = None\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def reset_episode(self):\\n\",\n    \"        self._hidden = torch.zeros(1, self.hidden_dim, device=next(self.parameters()).device)\\n\",\n    \"        self._step = 0; self._pending_write_key = None; self._prev_emb = None\\n\",\n    \"        self.memory.reset(); self.budget._reset()\\n\",\n    \"        if hasattr(self.routing, 'reset'): self.routing.reset()\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def prime_oracle_schedule(self, actions): self._primed_oracle_actions = actions\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    def forward(self, token_id, route_stop_grad=True, ablation_no_mem=False,\\n\",\n    \"                ablation_rand_routing=False):\\n\",\n    \"        if self._hidden is None: self.reset_episode()\\n\",\n    \"        device = token_id.device\\n\",\n    \"        t = self._step; self._step += 1\\n\",\n    \"        is_query_step = (t >= QUERY_START)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        emb = self.embedding(token_id.view(1) if token_id.dim()==0 else token_id).squeeze(0)\\n\",\n    \"        budget_norm = self.budget.budget_remaining_normalised\\n\",\n    \"        _O2I = {'SKIP': 0, 'READ': 1, 'WRITE': 2, 'PERCEIVE': 3}\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        if self._primed_oracle_actions and t < len(self._primed_oracle_actions):\\n\",\n    \"            action_idx = _O2I.get(self._primed_oracle_actions[t], 0)\\n\",\n    \"            hfr = self._hidden  # oracle routing: full gradient\\n\",\n    \"            lr, _, ls = self.routing(hfr, budget_norm, t/EPISODE_LENGTH, float(t%2), float(is_query_step))\\n\",\n    \"        elif ablation_rand_routing:\\n\",\n    \"            action_idx = random.randint(0, 2)\\n\",\n    \"            lr = torch.zeros(3, device=device); ls = 1.0/3\\n\",\n    \"        else:\\n\",\n    \"            hfr = self._hidden.detach() if route_stop_grad else self._hidden\\n\",\n    \"            lr, action_idx, ls = self.routing(hfr, budget_norm, t/EPISODE_LENGTH, float(t%2), float(is_query_step))\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        if action_idx == 3:\\n\",\n    \"            self._pending_write_key = emb.detach().clone(); action_idx = 0\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        _act_before = action_idx\\n\",\n    \"        permitted = self.budget.step(0 if action_idx==3 else action_idx)  # PERCEIVE(3) is no-op on budget\\n\",\n    \"        if not permitted: action_idx = 0\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        retrieved = torch.zeros(self.d_embed, device=device)\\n\",\n    \"        if action_idx == 1 and not ablation_no_mem:\\n\",\n    \"            retrieved, _ = self.memory.read(emb); retrieved = retrieved.to(device)\\n\",\n    \"        elif action_idx == 2 and not ablation_no_mem:\\n\",\n    \"            wk = self._pending_write_key if self._pending_write_key is not None \\\\\\n\",\n    \"                 else (self._prev_emb if self._prev_emb is not None else emb)\\n\",\n    \"            ws = ls if self._primed_oracle_actions else 1.0\\n\",\n    \"            self.memory.write(wk, emb, salience=ws); self._pending_write_key = None\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        self._hidden = self.gru(torch.cat([emb, retrieved], dim=-1).unsqueeze(0), self._hidden)\\n\",\n    \"        self._prev_emb = emb.detach().clone()\\n\",\n    \"        logits = self.output_head(torch.cat([self._hidden.squeeze(0), retrieved], dim=-1))\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"        info = {\\n\",\n    \"            'step': t,\\n\",\n    \"            'action': {0:'SKIP',1:'READ',2:'WRITE'}.get(action_idx,'SKIP'),\\n\",\n    \"            'action_idx': action_idx,\\n\",\n    \"            'blocked': (not permitted) and _act_before in (1,2),\\n\",\n    \"            'permitted': permitted,\\n\",\n    \"            'salience_entropy': ls,\\n\",\n    \"            'budget_remaining': self.budget.budget_remaining,\\n\",\n    \"            'occupancy': self.memory.occupancy,\\n\",\n    \"            'routing_logits': lr}\\n\",\n    \"        return logits, info\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"print('ArchitectureB loaded OK')\\n\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n   \"execution_count\": null,\n   \"id\": \"741d164f\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"outputs\": [\n    {\n     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n     \"text\": [\n      \"Episode: 190 tokens, 20 key-value pairs\\n\",\n      \"Sample oracle: ['PERCEIVE', 'WRITE', 'PERCEIVE', 'WRITE', 'PERCEIVE', 'WRITE', 'PERCEIVE', 'WRITE']\\n\"\n     ]\n    }\n   ],\n   \"source\": [\n    \"from dataclasses import dataclass\\n\",\n    \"from typing import List\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"N_GENUINE = 20; EPISODE_LENGTH = 190; QUERY_START = 150\\n\",\n    \"IGNORE_INDEX = -100\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"@dataclass\\n\",\n    \"class Episode:\\n\",\n    \"    input_ids: torch.Tensor\\n\",\n    \"    oracle_actions: List[str]\\n\",\n    \"    target_value_ids: torch.Tensor\\n\",\n    \"    genuine_keys: List[int] = None\\n\",\n    \"    genuine_values: List[int] = None\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"def generate_episode(seed=0):\\n\",\n    \"    rng = random.Random(seed)\\n\",\n    \"    gk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\\n\",\n    \"    gv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\\n\",\n    \"    fk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\\n\",\n    \"    fv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    inp, ora = [], []\\n\",\n    \"    # Encode: 100 steps (50 key+value pairs)\\n\",\n    \"    for i in range(100):\\n\",\n    \"        if i % 2 == 0:\\n\",\n    \"            inp.append(gk[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fk[i//2])\\n\",\n    \"            ora.append('PERCEIVE' if i//2 < N_GENUINE else 'SKIP')\\n\",\n    \"        else:\\n\",\n    \"            inp.append(gv[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fv[i//2])\\n\",\n    \"            ora.append('WRITE' if i//2 < N_GENUINE else 'SKIP')\\n\",\n    \"    # Delay: 50 steps\\n\",\n    \"    for _ in range(50):\\n\",\n    \"        inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49)); ora.append('SKIP')\\n\",\n    \"    # Query: 20 steps\\n\",\n    \"    tv = [IGNORE_INDEX] * EPISODE_LENGTH\\n\",\n    \"    for qi, qk in enumerate(gk):\\n\",\n    \"        inp.append(qk); inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49))\\n\",\n    \"        ora.extend(['READ', 'SKIP'])\\n\",\n    \"        tv[150 + qi*2] = gv[qi]\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    return Episode(\\n\",\n    \"        input_ids=torch.tensor(inp, dtype=torch.long),\\n\",\n    \"        oracle_actions=ora,\\n\",\n    \"        target_value_ids=torch.tensor(tv, dtype=torch.long),\\n\",\n    \"        genuine_keys=gk, genuine_values=gv)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"ep = generate_episode(0)\\n\",\n    \"print(f'Episode: {len(ep.input_ids)} tokens, {N_GENUINE} key-value pairs')\\n\",\n    \"print(f'Sample oracle: {ep.oracle_actions[:8]}')\\n\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n   \"execution_count\": null,\n   \"id\": \"7b05f1f6\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"outputs\": [\n    {\n     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n     \"text\": [\n      \"Trainer class OK\\n\"\n     ]\n    }\n   ],\n   \"source\": [\n    \"import wandb\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"class SRMoETrainer:\\n\",\n    \"    def __init__(self, model, lr=3e-3, lambda_route=1.0, lambda_div=0.1,\\n\",\n    \"                 lambda_margin=1.0, margin_target=0.5,\\n\",\n    \"                 route_class_weights=[1.0, 10.0, 15.0]):\\n\",\n    \"        self.model = model.to(DEVICE)\\n\",\n    \"        self.lr = lr; self.lambda_route = lambda_route\\n\",\n    \"        self.lambda_div = lambda_div; self.lambda_margin = lambda_margin\\n\",\n    \"        self.margin_target = margin_target\\n\",\n    \"        self.route_class_weights = route_class_weights\\n\",\n    \"        self.params = list(model.routing.parameters()) + list(model.output_head.parameters())\\n\",\n\n[533 more lines in file. Use offset=501 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774331544047}}
{"type":"message","id":"eae47e11","parentId":"1f9132e4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:52:54.328Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of all the code. Let me make the targeted fixes:\n\n1. **Fix 1: In `ArchitectureB.forward()`, don't detach hidden state in Phase 1 when not using oracle routing**\n   - The `route_stop_grad=True` default means during Phase 1, the router gets zero task gradient\n   - Change to `route_stop_grad=False` by default, or better: the trainer should pass `route_stop_grad=False`\n\n2. **Fix 2: In trainer, pass `route_stop_grad=False` during Phase 1**\n   - The router learns from task loss + CE loss together\n   - Only detach during Phase 2 when imitation learning\n\n3. **Fix 3: Mix query-phase oracle into Phase 1 training**\n   - During Phase 1, gradually increase the fraction of steps where we use real routing on query phases\n   - Or: after the first few hundred episodes, start using real routing even during some encode phases\n\n4. **Fix 4: Phase 2 soft transition**\n   - Instead of hard switch from oracle to no oracle, gradually reduce the probability of using oracle\n   - Or: use a curriculum that starts with mostly oracle and slowly transitions\n\n5. **Fix 5: Add minimum route density penalty**\n   - Penalize models where non-SKIP fraction is below some threshold\n   - This ensures the router learns to take actions\n\n6. **Fix 6: Include ALL steps in route CE loss (not just non-IGNORE_INDEX)**\n   - The current code does `ignore_index=IGNORE_INDEX` which means SKIP steps during query phase don't contribute to routing loss\n   - Wait, actually the oracle_actions at query steps are READ/SKIP, so those are labeled. The problem is the detaching.\n\nLet me now make targeted edits. The main ones are:\n1. Change `route_stop_grad=True` to `route_stop_grad=False` in the trainer's `train_episode`\n2. Add a minimum route density penalty in the trainer\n3. Add soft transition for Phase 2\n4. During Phase 1, gradually introduce non-oracle routing on query steps\n\nI'm identifying the key changes needed: removing the gradient stop on the hidden state during Phase 1, introducing a density penalty to encourage non-SKIP actions, and implementing a gradual transition between phases rather than a hard switch.","thinkingSignature":"63c1b7e04a65ae235ebd8499425674fe3a50e5a71e43ba562e7da384e3a98a95"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll make the targeted fixes. Let me write the updated cells:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zag6nn7wmhg6_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb","oldText":"        self.params = list(model.routing.parameters()) + list(model.output_head.parameters())\n        self.opt = torch.optim.Adam(self.params, lr=lr)","newText":"        self.params = (\n            list(model.routing.parameters())\n            + list(model.output_head.parameters())\n            + list(model.gru.parameters())  # GRU gets gradient too (for Fix #1)\n        )\n        self.opt = torch.optim.Adam(self.params, lr=lr)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":104881,"output":645,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119518,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774331544078}}
