{"type":"message","id":"4ed6a53b","parentId":"126e8493","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:57:00.904Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I need to re-check the fix_srmoe.py - I replaced all the `✓` checkmarks. But there's still one issue: the `route_mask` logic has a variable name conflict - I'm iterating with `for ti, oa in enumerate(oracle_labels)` but `oa` is already the integer index (0,1,2), not the original string. Let me re-read my fix:\n\n```python\nfor ti, oa in enumerate(oracle_labels):\n    if oa == IGNORE_INDEX:\n        route_mask[ti] = False\n    elif oa == 0 and ti < QUERY_START:  # SKIP during encode -- skip this label\n        route_mask[ti] = False\n```\n\nThis looks correct - `oracle_labels` contains the integer indices, so `oa` is 0/1/2 or IGNORE_INDEX. Let me run the script.","thinkingSignature":"55756d8b2bd71b6cd7c752906a84db45b9007c154a2bf998fad8259dc953e518"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mvpwslwi4ym2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\fix_srmoe.py 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":100632,"output":246,"cacheRead":13992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114870,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774331812643}}
