{"type":"message","id":"0bce0ed7","parentId":"93255cdd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:05:13.870Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `kimi` provider isn't being found. The issue is the config format. Looking at the schema example:\n```yaml\nproviders:\n  kimi:\n    apiKey: ...\n    baseURL: ...\n    models:\n      moonshot-v1-8k: moonshot-v1-8k\n```\n\nBut the existing `moonshot-sandbox` model uses `moonshot/v1/chat/completions` as the model name within the provider. Let me look at the schema reference more carefully.\n\nActually, the schema for providers shows:\n```yaml\nproviders:\n  kimi:\n    apiKey: ... # Moonshot AI / Kimi API key\n    baseURL: https://api.moonshot.cn/openapi/v1 # Kimi base URL\n    models:\n      moonshot-v1-8k: moonshot-v1-8k # maps OpenClaw model ID to provider model ID\n```\n\nSo `kimi/moonshot-v1-8k` should work if the provider is properly registered. But the error says \"provider not found: kimi\". Let me check if the config is actually loading the providers section. Maybe the config file format is wrong and it's not being parsed correctly.\n\nLet me check the raw config file.","thinkingSignature":"614d5a85dea07d4a59087fd911c9551e59756dca413bb8bbb08e54cc78d6c852"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_155sybpt4ltn_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.yaml"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":113444,"output":298,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":127917,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774353903810}}
