{"type":"message","id":"4bc0e828","parentId":"677e62e4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:05:25.177Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config file looks correct. The `providers` section has `kimi` with the API key and base URL. But `openclaw config show` doesn't show the `providers` section in its output. Let me check if the config is being loaded properly by checking the effective config.\n\nAlso, looking at the `moonshot-sandbox` model: it uses `moonshot/v1/chat/completions` which is a provider-relative path. This means the actual model ID sent to the provider is `{baseURL}/v1/chat/completions` = `https://api.moonshot.cn/openapi/v1/v1/chat/completions` which is WRONG.\n \nI see the issue now — the baseURL already includes `/openapi/v1`, so appending `/v1/chat/completions` creates a duplicate path segment. The model configuration should just be `chat/completions` to avoid this duplication. Let me update that and test it out.","thinkingSignature":"15a75c38f0c01fbb0e97fc0ce3980f568b999e43d3ea327d0506f31a61ea45b8"},{"type":"text","text":"The `moonshot-sandbox` model has a path duplication issue — let me fix it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_he36m5qcw9uz_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.yaml","oldText":"    moonshot-sandbox:\n      provider: moonshot\n      model: moonshot/v1/chat/completions\n      apiKey: ${KIMI_BOT_TOKEN}","newText":"    moonshot-sandbox:\n      provider: kimi\n      model: moonshot-v1-8k"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":113767,"output":341,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128283,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774353914099}}
